obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25099)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25099&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Narcotic Drugs and`
  line `Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2[and it applies also--`
  line
  line `(a) to all citizens of India outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) to all persons on ships and aircrafts registered in India,`
  line
  line `wherever they may be.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and for`
  line `different States and any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be`
  line `construed in relation to any State as a reference to the coming into force of that provision in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. 14th November, 1985, vide notification No. S.O. 821(E), dated 14th November, 1985, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25100)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25100&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(i) "addict" means a person who has dependence on any narcotic drug or psychotropic`
  line substance;]
  line
  line `(ii) "Board" means the Central Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central`
  line `Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963);`
  line
  line `(iii) "cannabis (hemp)" means--`
  line
  line `(a) charas, that is, the separated resin, in whatever form, whether crude or purified, obtained`
  line `from the cannabis plant and also includes concentrated preparation and resin known as hashish oil`
  line `or liquid hashish;`
  line
  line `(b) ganja, that is, the flowering or fruiting tops of the cannabis plant (excluding the seeds and`
  line `leaves when not accompanied by the tops), by whatever name they may be known or designated;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) any mixture, with or without any neutral material, of any of the above forms of cannabis`
  line `or any rink prepared therefrom;`
  line
  line `(iv) "cannabis plant" means any plant of the genus cannabis;`
  line
  line `^2[(iva) "Central Government factories" means factories owned by the Central Government or`
  line `factories owned by any company in which the Central Government holds at least fifty-one per cent. of`
  line `the paid-up share capital;]`
  line
  line `(v) "coca derivative" means--`
  line
  line `(a) crude cocaine, that is, any extract of coca leaf which can be used, directly or indirectly,`
  line `for the manufacture of cocaine;`
  line
  line `(b) ecgonine and all the derivatives of ecgonine from which it can be recovered;`
  line
  line `(c) cocaine, that is, methyl ester of benzoyl-ecgonine and its salts; and`
  line
  line `(d) all preparations containing more than 0.1 per cent. of cocaine;`
  line
  line `(vi) "coca leaf" means--`
  line
  line `(a) the leaf of the coca plant except a leaf from which all ecgonine, cocaine and any other`
  line `ecgonine alkaloids have been removed;`
  line
  line `(b) any mixture thereof with or without any neutral material,`
  line
  line `but does not include any preparation containing not more than 0.1 per cent. of cocaine;`
  line
  line `(vii) "coca plant" means the plant of any species of the genus Frythroxylon;`
  line
  line `^3[(viia) "commercial quantity", in relation to narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances, means`
  line `any quantity greater than the quantity specified by the Central Government by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(viib) "controlled delivery" means the technique of allowing illicit or suspect consignments of`
  line `narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances, controlled substances or substances substituted for them to`
  line `pass out of, or through or into the territory of India with the knowledge and under the supervision of`
  line `an officer empowered in this behalf or duly authorised under section 50A with a view to identifying`
  line `the persons involved in the commission of an offence under this Act;`
  line
  line `(viic) "corresponding law" means any law corresponding to the provisions of this Act;]`
  line
  line `^4[^5[(viid)] "controlled substance" means any substance which the Central Government may,`
  line `having regard to the available information as to its possible use in the production or manufacture of`
  line `narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances or to the provisions of any International Convention, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a controlled substance;]`
  line
  line `(viii) "conveyance" means a conveyance of any description whatsoever and includes any aircraft,`
  line `vehicle or vessel;`
  line
  line `^2[(viiia) "essential narcotic drug" means a narcotic drug notified by the Central Government for`
  line `medical and scientific use;]`
  line
  line `^4[^6[(viiib)] "illicit traffic", in relation to narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances, means--`
  line
  line `(i) cultivating any coca plant or gathering any portion of coca plant;`
  line
  line `(ii) cultivating the opium poppy or any cannabis plant;`
  line
  line `(iii) engaging in the production, manufacture, possession, sale, purchase, transportation,`
  line `warehousing, concealment, use or consumption, import inter-State, export inter-State, import into`
  line `India, export from India or transhipment, of narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances;`
  line
  line `(iv) dealing in any activities in narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances other than those`
  line `referred to in sub-clauses (i) to (iii); or`
  line
  line `(v) handling or letting out any premises for the carrying on of any of the activities referred to`
  line `in sub-clauses (i) to (iv),`
  line
  line `other than those permitted under this Act, or any rule or order made, or any condition of any licence,`
  line `term or authorisation issued, thereunder, and includes--`
  line
  line `(1) financing, directly or indirectly, any of the aforementioned activities;`
  line
  line `(2) abetting or conspiring in the furtherance of or in support of doing any of the`
  line `aforementioned activities; and`
  line
  line `(3) harbouring persons engaged in any of the afore-mentioned activities;]`
  line
  line `(ix) "International Convention" means--`
  line
  line `(a) the Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs, 1961 adopted by the United Nations`
  line `Conference at New York in March, 1961;`
  line
  line `(b) the Protocol, amending the Convention mentioned in sub-clause (a), adopted by the`
  line `United Nations Conference at Geneva in March, 1972;`
  line
  line `(c) the Convention on Psychotropic Substances, 1971 adopted by the United Nations`
  line `Conference at Vienna in February, 1971; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other international convention, or protocol or other instrument amending an`
  line `international convention, relating to narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances which may be`
  line `ratified or acceded to by India after the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(x) "manufacture", in relation to narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances, includes--`
  line
  line `(1) all processes other than production by which such drugs or substances may be obtained;`
  line
  line `(2) refining of such drugs or substances;`
  line
  line `(3) transformation of such drugs or substances; and`
  line
  line `(4) making of preparation (otherwise than in a pharmacy on prescription) with or containing`
  line
  line `such drugs or substances;`
  line
  line `(xi) "manufactured drug" means--`
  line
  line `(a) all coca derivatives, medicinal cannabis, opium derivatives and poppy straw concentrate;`
  line
  line `(b) any other narcotic substance or preparation which the Central Government may, having`
  line `regard to the available information as to its nature or to a decision, if any, under any International`
  line `Convention, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a manufactured drug,`
  line
  line `but does not include any narcotic substance or preparation which the Central Government may, having`
  line `regard to the available information as to its nature or to a decision, if any, under any International`
  line `Convention, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare not to be a manufactured drug;`
  line
  line `(xii) "medicinal cannabis", that is, medicinal hemp, means any extract or tincture of cannabis`
  line `(hemp);`
  line
  line `(xiii) "Narcotics Commissioner" means the Narcotics Commissioner appointed under section 5;`
  line
  line `(xiv) "narcotic drug" means coca leaf, cannabis (hemp), opium, popy straw and includes all`
  line `manufactured drugs;`
  line
  line `(xv) "opium" means--`
  line
  line `(a) the coagulated juice of the opium poppy; and`
  line
  line `(b) any mixture, with or without any neutral material, of the coagulated juice of the opium`
  line poppy,
  line
  line `but does not include any preparation containing not more than 0.2 per cent. of morphine;`
  line
  line `(xvi) "opium derivative" means--`
  line
  line `(a) medicinal opium, that is, opium which has undergone the processes necessary to adapt it`
  line `for medicinal use in accordance with the requirements of the Indian Pharmacopoeia or any other`
  line `pharmacopoeia notified in this behalf by the Central Government, whether in powder form or`
  line `granulated or otherwise or mixed with neutral materials;`
  line
  line `(b) prepared opium, that is, any product of opium obtained by any series of operations`
  line `designed to transform opium into an extract suitable for smoking and the dross or other residue`
  line `remaining after opium is smoked;`
  line
  line `(c) phenanthrene alkaloids, namely, morphine, codeine, thebaine and their salts;`
  line
  line `(d) diacetylmorphine, that is, the alkaloid also known as dia-morphine or heroin and its salts;`
  line and
  line
  line `(e) all preparations containing more than 0.2 per cent. of morphine or containing any`
  line diacetylmorphine;
  line
  line `(xvii) "opium poppy" means--`
  line
  line `(a) the plant of the species Papaver somniferum L; and`
  line
  line `(b) the plant of any other species of Papaver from which opium or any phenanthrene alkaloid`
  line `can be extracted and which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare to be opium poppy for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(xviii) "poppy straw" means all parts (except the seeds) of the opium poppy after harvesting`
  line `whether in their original form or cut, crushed or powdered and whether or not juice has been`
  line `extracted therefrom;`
  line
  line `(xix) "poppy straw concentrate" means the material arising when poppy straw has entered into a`
  line `process for the concentration of its alkaloids;`
  line
  line `(xx) "preparation", in relation to a narcotic drug or psychotropic substance, means any one or`
  line `more such drugs or substances in dosage form or any solution or mixture, in whatever physical state,`
  line `containing one or more such drugs or substances;`
  line
  line `(xxi) "Prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xxii) "production" means separation of opium, poppy straw, coca leaves or cannabis from the`
  line `plants from which they are obtained;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) "Psychotropic substance" means any substance, natural or synthetic, or any natural`
  line `material or any salt or preparation of such substance or material included in the list of psychotropic`
  line `substances specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `^7[(xxiiia) "small quantity", in relation to narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances, means any`
  line `quantity lesser than the quantity specified by the Central Government by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette;]
  line
  line `(xxiv) "to import inter-State" means to bring into a State or Union territory in India from another`
  line `State or Union territory in India;`
  line
  line `(xxv) "to import into India", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means to`
  line `bring into India from a place outside India and includes the bringing into any port or airport or place`
  line `in India of a narcotic drug or a psychotropic substance intended to be taken out of India without being`
  line `removed from the vessel, aircraft, vehicle or any other conveyance in which it is being carried.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause and clause (xxvi), "India" includes the territorial`
  line `waters of India.`
  line
  line `(xxvi) "to export from India", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means to`
  line `take out of India to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) "to export inter-State" means to take out of a State or Union territory in India to another`
  line `State or Union territory in India;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) "to transport" means to take from one place to another within the same State or Union`
  line territory;
  line
  line `^8[(xxviiia) "use", in relation to narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances, means any kind of use`
  line `except personal consumption;]`
  line
  line `(xxix) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Code.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of clauses (v), (vi), (xv) and (xvi) the percentages in the case of liquid`
  line `preparations shall be calculated on the basis that a preparation containing one per cent. of a substance`
  line `means a preparation in which one gram of substance, if solid, or one mililitre of substance, if liquid, is`
  line `contained in every one hundred mililitre of the preparation and so on in proportion for any greater or less`
  line `percentage:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, having regard to the developments in the field of methods`
  line `of calculating percentages in liquid preparations prescribe, by rules, any other basis which it may deem`
  line `appropriate for such calculation.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 3, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 3 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (viia) relettered as clause (viid) thereof by Act 9 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line `6. Clause (viiia) relettered as clause (viiib) thereof by Act 16 of 2014, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 3 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25101)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to add to or omit from the list of psychotropic substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25101&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `may, if satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do on the basis of--`
  line
  line `(a) the information and evidence which has become available to it with respect to the nature and`
  line `effects of, and the abuse or the scope for abuse of, any substance (natural or synthetic) or natural`
  line `material or any salt or preparation of such substance or material; and`
  line
  line `(b) the modifications or provisions (if any) which have been made to, or in, any International`
  line `Convention with respect to such substance, natural material or salt or preparation of such substance or`
  line material,
  line
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, add to, or, as the case may be, omit from, the list of psychotropic`
  line `substances specified in the Schedule such substance or natural material or salt or preparation of such`
  line `substance or material.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25102)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Central Government to take measures for preventing and combating abuse of and illicit traffic in narcotic drugs, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25102&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government shall`
  line `take all such measures as it deems necessary or expedient for the purpose of preventing and combating`
  line `abuse of narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances and the illicit traffic therein ^1[and for ensuring their`
  line `medical and scientific use].`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `measures which the Central Government may take under that sub-section include measures with respect`
  line `to all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) coordination of actions by various officers, State Governments and other authorities--`
  line
  line `(i) under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(ii) under any other law for the time being in force in connection with the enforcement of the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) obligations under the International Conventions;`
  line
  line `(c) assistance to the concerned authorities in foreign countries and concerned international`
  line `organisations with a view to facilitating coordination and universal action for prevention and`
  line `suppression of illicit traffic in narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances;`
  line
  line `(d) identification, treatment, education, after care, rehabilitation and social re-integration of`
  line addicts;
  line
  line `^2[(da) availability of narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances for medical and scientific use;]`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as the Central Government deems necessary or expedient for the purpose of`
  line `securing the effective implementation of the provisions of this Act and preventing and combating the`
  line `abuse of narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances and illicit traffic therein.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, by order, published in the Official Gazette, constitute an authority or a hierarchy of authorities`
  line `by such name or names as may be specified in the order for the purpose of exercising such of the powers`
  line `and functions of the Central Government under this Act and for taking measures with respect to such of`
  line `the matters referred to in sub-section (2) as may be mentioned in the order, and subject to the supervision`
  line `and control of the Central Government and the provisions of such order, such authority or authorities may`
  line `exercise the powers and take the measures so mentioned in the order as if such authority or authorities had`
  line `been empowered by this Act to exercise those powers and take such measures.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25103)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Officers of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25103&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 4, the Central Government shall appoint a Narcotics Commissioner and may also appoint such`
  line `other officers with such designations as it thinks fit for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Narcotics Commissioner shall, either by himself or through officers subordinate to him,`
  line `exercise all powers and perform all functions relating to the superintendence of the cultivation of the`
  line `opium poppy and production of opium and shall also exercise and perform such other powers and`
  line `functions as may be entrusted to him by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers appointed under sub-section (1) shall be subject to the general control and direction`
  line `of the Central Government, or, if so directed by that Government, also of the Board or any other authority`
  line `or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25104)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `The Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropie Substances Consultative Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25104&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may constitute, by notification in the Official Gazette, an advisory committee to be called`
  line `"The Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Consultative Committee" (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the Committee) to advise the Central Government on such matters relating to the`
  line `administration of this Act as are referred to it by that Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall consist of a Chairman and such other members, not exceeding twenty, as`
  line `may be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall meet when required to do so by the Central Government and shall have`
  line `power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee may, if it deems it necessary so to do for the efficient discharge of any of its`
  line `functions, constitute one or more sub-committees and may appoint to any such sub-committee, whether`
  line `generally or for the consideration of any particular matter, any person (including a non-official) who is`
  line `not a member of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of, the manner of filling casual vacancies in the offices of and the allowances,`
  line `if any, payable to, the Chairman and other members of the Committee, and the conditions and restrictions`
  line `subject to which the Committee may appoint a person who is not a member of the Committee as a`
  line `member of any of its sub-committees, shall be such as may be prescribed by rules made by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25105)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Officers of State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25105&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint such officers with such`
  line `designations as it thinks fit for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers appointed under sub-section (1) shall be subject to the general control and direction`
  line `of the State Government, or, if so directed by that Government, also of any other authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (25106)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `National Fund for Control of Drug Abuse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25106&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. National Fund for Control of Drug Abuse.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, constitute a Fund to be called the National Fund for Control of Drug Abuse`
  line `(hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the Fund) and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) an amount which the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament`
  line `by law in this behalf, provide;`
  line
  line `(b) the sale proceeds of any property forfeited under Chapter VA;`
  line
  line `(c) any grants that may be made by any person or institution;`
  line
  line `(d) any income from investment of the amounts credited to the Fund under the aforesaid`
  line provisions.
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Fund shall be applied by the Central Government to meet the expenditure incurred in`
  line `connection with the measures taken for--`
  line
  line `(a) combating illicit traffic in narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances or controlled substances;`
  line
  line `(b) controlling the abuse of narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances;`
  line
  line `(c) identifying, treating, rehabilitating addicts;`
  line
  line `(d) preventing drug abuse;`
  line
  line `(e) educating public against drug abuse;`
  line
  line `(f) supplying drugs to addicts where such supply is a medical necessity.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may constitute a Governing Body as it thinks fit to advise that`
  line `Government and to sanction money out of the said Fund subject to the limit notified by the Central`
  line `Government in the Official Gazette.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Governing Body shall consist of a Chairman (not below the rank of an Additional Secretary`
  line `to the Central Government) and such other members not exceeding six as the Central Government may`
  line appoint.
  line
  line `(5) The Governing Body shall have the power to regulate its own procedure.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 4, for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_b:
  sectionId (25107)
  sectionNo 7B
  orderNo 9
  title `Annual report of activities financed under the Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25107&sectionno=7B&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[7B. Annual report of activities financed under the Fund.--The Central Government shall, as soon`
  line `as may be, after the end of each financial year, cause to be published in the Official Gazette, a report`
  line `giving an account of the activities financed under section 7A during the financial year, together with a`
  line `statement of accounts.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25108)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Prohibition of certain operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 5 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25108&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) cultivate any coca plant or gather any portion of coca plant; or`
  line
  line `(b) cultivate the opium poppy or any cannabis plant; or`
  line
  line `(c) produce, manufacture, possess, sell, purchase, transport, warehouse, use, consume, import`
  line `inter-State, export inter-State, import into India, export from India or tranship any narcotic drug or`
  line `psychotropic substance,`
  line `except for medical or scientific purposes and in the manner and to the extent provided by the provisions`
  line `of this Act or the rules or orders made thereunder and in a case where any such provision, imposes any`
  line `requirement by way of licence, permit or authorisation also in accordance with the terms and conditions`
  line `of such licence, permit or authorisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that, and subject to the other provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the`
  line `prohibition against the cultivation of the cannabis plant for the production of ganja or the production,`
  line `possession, use, consumption, purchase, sale, transport, warehousing, import inter-State and export`
  line `inter-State of ganja for any purpose other than medical and scientific purpose shall take effect only from`
  line `the date which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that nothing in this section shall apply to the export of poppy straw for decorative`
  line purposes.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (25109)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 11
  title `Prohibition of certain activities relating to property derived from offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25109&sectionno=8A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[A. Prohibition of certain activities relating to property derived from offence.-- No person`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) convert or transfer any property knowing that such property is derived from an offence`
  line `committed under this Act or under any other corresponding law of any other country or from an act of`
  line `participation in such offence, for the purpose of concealing or disguising the illicit origin of the`
  line `property or to assist any person in the commission of an offence or to evade the legal consequences;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) conceal or disguise the true nature, source, location, disposition of any property knowing that`
  line `such property is derived from an offence committed under this Act or under any other corresponding`
  line `law of any other country; or`
  line
  line `(c) knowingly acquire, possess or use any property which was derived from an offence committed`
  line `under this Act or under any other corresponding law of any other country.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25110)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Central Government to permit, control and regulate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25110&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions`
  line `of section 8, the Central Government may, by rules--`
  line
  line `(a) permit and regulate--`
  line
  line `(i) the cultivation, or gathering of any portion (such cultivation or gathering being only on`
  line `account of the Central Government) of coca plant, or the production, possession, sale, purchase,`
  line `transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, use or consumption of coca leaves;`
  line
  line `(ii) the cultivation (such cultivation being only on account of Central Government) of the`
  line `opium poppy;`
  line
  line `(iii) the production and manufacture of opium and production of poppy straw;`
  line
  line `^1[(iiia) the possession, transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, warehousing, sale,`
  line `purchase, consumption and use of poppy straw produced from plants from which no juice has`
  line `been extracted through lancing;]`
  line
  line `(iv) the sale of opium and opium derivatives from the Central Government factories for`
  line `export from India or sale to State Government or to manufacturing chemists;`
  line
  line `(v) the manufacture of manufactured drugs (other than prepared opium) but not including`
  line `manufacture of medicinal opium or any preparation containing any manufactured drug from`
  line `materials which the maker is lawfully entitled to possess;`
  line
  line `^1[(va) the manufacture, possession, transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, sale,`
  line `purchase, consumption and use of essential narcotic drugs:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, in respect of an essential narcotic drug, the State Government has`
  line `granted licence or permit under the provisions of section 10 prior to the commencement of the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances (Amendment) Act, 2014 (16 of 2014), such`
  line `licence or permit shall continue to be valid till the date of its expiry or for a period of twelve`
  line `months from such commencement, whichever is earlier.]`
  line
  line `(vi) the manufacture, possession, transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, sale,`
  line `purchase, consumption or use of psychotropic substances;`
  line
  line `(vii) the import into India and export from India and transhipment of narcotic drugs and`
  line `psychotropic substances;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe any other matter requisite to render effective the control of the Central Government`
  line `over any of the matters specified in clause (a).`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line
  line `(a) empower the Central Government to fix from time to time the limits within which licences`
  line `may be given for the cultivation of the opium poppy;`
  line
  line `(b) require that all opium, the produce of land cultivated with the opium poppy, shall be delivered`
  line `by the cultivators to the officers authorised in this behalf by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the forms and conditions of licences for cultivation of the opium poppy and for`
  line `production and manufacture of opium; the fees that may be charged therefor; the authorities by which`
  line `such licences may be granted, withheld, refused or cancelled and the authorities before which appeals`
  line `against the orders of withholding, refusal or cancellation of licences shall lie;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribe that opium shall be weighed, examined and classified according to its quality and`
  line `consistence by the officers authorised in this behalf by the Central Government in the presence of the`
  line `cultivator at the time of delivery by the cultivator;`
  line
  line `(e) empower the Central Government to fix from time to time the price to be paid to the`
  line `cultivators for the opium delivered;`
  line
  line `(f) provide for the weighment, examination and classification, according to the quality and`
  line `consistence, of the opium received at the factory and the deductions from or additions (if any) to the`
  line `standard price to be made in accordance with the result of such examination; and the authorities by`
  line `which the decisions with regard to the weighment, examination, classification, deductions or`
  line `additions shall be made and the authorities before which appeals against such decisions shall lie;`
  line
  line `(g) require that opium delivered by a cultivator, if found as a result of examination in the Central`
  line `Government factory to be adulterated, may be confiscated by the officers authorised in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(h) prescribe the forms and conditions of licences for the manufacture of manufactured drugs, the`
  line `authorities by which such licences may be granted and the fees that may be charged therefor;`
  line
  line `^2[(ha) prescribe the forms and conditions of licences or permits for the manufacture, possession,`
  line `transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, sale, purchase, consumption or use of essential`
  line `narcotic drugs, the authorities by which such licence or permit may be granted and the fees that may`
  line `be charged therefor;]`
  line
  line `(i) prescribe the forms and conditions of licences or permits for the manufacture, possession,`
  line `transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, sale, purchase, consumption or use of psychotropic`
  line `substances, the authorities by which such licences or permits may be granted and the fees that may be`
  line `charged therefor;`
  line
  line `(j) prescribe the ports and other places at which any kind of narcotic drugs or psychotropic`
  line `substances may be imported into India or exported from India or transhipped; the forms and`
  line `conditions of certificates, authorisations or permits, as the case may be, for such import, export or`
  line `transhipment; the authorities by which such certificates, authorisations or permits may be granted and`
  line `the fees that may be charged therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (25111)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to control and regulate controlled substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 6 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25111&sectionno=9A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Power to control and regulate controlled substances.-- (1) If the Central Government is of`
  line `the opinion that, having regard to the use of any controlled substance in the production or manufacture of`
  line `any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance, it is necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, it`
  line `may, by order, provide for regulating or prohibiting the production, manufacture, supply and distribution`
  line `thereof and trade and commerce therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the power conferred by sub-section (1), an order made`
  line `thereunder may provide for regulating by licences, permits or otherwise, the production, manufacture,`
  line `possession, transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, sale, purchase, consumption, use, storage,`
  line `distribution, disposal or acquisition of any controlled substance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25112)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of State Government to permit, control and regulate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25112&sectionno=10&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 8, the State Government may, by rules--`
  line
  line `(a) permit and regulate--`
  line
  line `(i) the possession, transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, warehousing, sale,`
  line `purchase, consumption and use of poppy straw ^1[except poppy straw produced from plants from`
  line `which no juice has been extracted through lancing;]`
  line
  line `(ii) the possession, transport, import inter-State, export inter-State, sale, purchase,`
  line `consumption and use of opium;`
  line
  line `(iii) the cultivation of any cannabis plant, production, manufacture, possession, transport,`
  line `import inter-State, export inter-State, sale, purchase, consumption or use of cannabis (excluding`
  line `charas);`
  line
  line `(iv) the manufacture of medicinal opium or any preparation containing any manufactured`
  line `drug from materials which the maker is lawfully entitled to possess;`
  line
  line `(v) the possession, transport, purchase, sale, import inter-State, export inter-State, use or`
  line `consumption of ^2[manufactured drugs (other than prepared opium and essential narcotic drugs)]`
  line `and of coca leaf and any preparation containing any manufactured drug;`
  line
  line `(vi) the manufacture and possession of prepared opium from opium lawfully possessed by an`
  line `addict registered with the State Government on medical advice for his personal consumption:`
  line
  line `Provided that save in so far as may be expressly provided in the rules made under sub-clauses (iv)`
  line `and (v), nothing in section 8 shall apply to the import inter-State, export inter-State, transport,`
  line `possession, purchase, sale, use or consumption of manufactured drugs which are the property and in`
  line `the possession of the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such drugs as are referred to in the preceding proviso shall not be sold or`
  line `otherwise delivered to any person who, under the rules made by the State Government under the`
  line `aforesaid sub-clauses, is not entitled to their possession;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe any other matter requisite to render effective the control of the State Government`
  line `over any of the matters specified in clause (a).`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) empower the State Government to declare any place to be a warehouse wherein it shall be the`
  line `duty of the owners to deposit all such poppy straw as is legally imported inter-State and is intended`
  line `for export inter-State or export from India; to regulate the safe custody of such poppy straw`
  line `warehoused and the removal of such poppy straw for sale or export inter-State or export from India;`
  line `to levy fees for such warehousing and to prescribe the manner in which and the period after which the`
  line `poppy straw warehoused shall be disposed of in default of payment of fees;`
  line
  line `(b) provide that the limits within which licences may be given for the cultivation of any cannabis`
  line `plant shall be fixed from time to time by or under the orders of the State Government;`
  line
  line `(c) provide that only the cultivators licenced by the prescribed authority of the State Government`
  line `shall be authorised to engage in cultivation of any cannabis plant;`
  line
  line `(d) require that all cannabis, the produce of land cultivated with cannabis plant, shall be delivered`
  line `by the cultivators to the officers of the State Government authorised in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(e) empower the State Government to fix from time to time, the price to be paid to the cultivators`
  line `for the cannabis delivered;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribe the forms and conditions of licences or permits for the purposes specified in`
  line `sub-clauses (i) to (vi) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) and the authorities by which such licences or`
  line `permits may be granted and the fees that may be charged therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "manufactured drugs other than prepared opium" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25113)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 15
  title `Narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances, etc., not liable to distress or attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25113&sectionno=11&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law or contract, no narcotic drug, psychotropic`
  line `substance, coca plant, the opium poppy or cannabis plant shall be liable to be distrained or attached by`
  line `any person for the recovery of any money under any order or decree of any court or authority or`
  line otherwise.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25114)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 16
  title `Restrictions over external dealings in narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25114&sectionno=12&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line No
  line `person shall engage in or control any trade whereby a narcotic drug or psychotropic substance is obtained`
  line `outside India and supplied to any person outside India save with the previous authorisation of the Central`
  line `Government and subject to such conditions as may be imposed by that Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25115)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 17
  title `Special provisions relating to coca plant and coca leaves for use in the preparation of flavouring agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25115&sectionno=13&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 8, the Central Government may`
  line `permit, with or without conditions, and on behalf of Government, the cultivation of any coca plant or`
  line `gathering of any portion thereof or the production, possession, sale, purchase, transport, import interState,`
  line `export inter-State or import into India of coca leaves for use in the preparation of any flavouring`
  line `agent which shall not contain any alkaloid and to the extent necessary for such use.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25116)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Special provision relating to cannabis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25116&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 8,`
  line `Government may, by general or special order and subject to such conditions as may be specified in such`
  line `order, allow cultivation of any cannabis plant for industrial purposes only of obtaining fibre or seed or for`
  line `horticultural purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25117)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `Punishment for contravention in relation to poppy straw.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25117&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Punishment for contravention in relation to poppy straw.-- Whoever, in contravention of`
  line `any provisions of this Act or any rule or order made or condition of a licence granted thereunder,`
  line `produces, possesses, transports, imports inter-State, exports inter-State, sells, purchases, uses or omits to`
  line `warehouse poppy straw or removes or does any act in respect of warehoused poppy straw shall be`
  line punishable,--
  line
  line `(a) where the contravention involves small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to ^2[one year], or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the contravention involves quantity lesser than commercial quantity but greater than`
  line `small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and with fine`
  line `which may extend to one lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) where the contravention involves commercial quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding`
  line `two lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 6, for sections 15 to 18 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 6, for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25118)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Punishment for contravention in relation to coca plant and coca leaves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 6, for sections 15 to 18 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25118&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Punishment for contravention in relation to coca plant and coca leaves.-- Whoever, in`
  line `contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule or order made or condition of licence granted`
  line `thereunder, cultivates any coca plant or gathers any portion of a coca plant or produces, possesses, sells,`
  line `purchases, transports, imports inter-State, exports inter-State or uses coca leaves shall be punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and with fine which may extend to one`
  line `lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25119)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Punishment for contravention in relation to prepared opium.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25119&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Punishment for contravention in relation to prepared opium.-- Whoever, in contravention of`
  line `any provision of this Act or any rule or order made or condition of licence granted thereunder,`
  line `manufactures, possesses, sells, purchases, transports, imports inter-State, exports inter-State or uses`
  line `prepared opium shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the contravention involves small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to ^2[one year], or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the contravention involves quantity lesser than commercial quantity but greater than`
  line `small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and with fine`
  line `which may extend to one lakh rupees; or`
  line
  line `(c) where the contravention involves commercial quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding`
  line `two lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 6, for sections 15 to 18 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 7, for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25120)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Punishment for contravention in relation to opium poppy and opium.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25120&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Punishment for contravention in relation to opium poppy and opium.--Whoever, in`
  line `contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule or order made or condition of licence granted`
  line `thereunder, cultivates the opium poppy or produces, manufactures, possesses, sells, purchases, transports,`
  line `imports inter-State, exports inter-State or uses opium shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the contravention involves small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to ^2[one year], or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the contravention involves commercial quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding`
  line `two lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment which may extend to ten years and with fine`
  line `which may extend to one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 6, for sections 15 to 18 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25121)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Punishment for embezzlement of opium by cultivator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25121&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any cultivator licensed to cultivate`
  line `the opium poppy on account of the Central Government who embezzles or otherwise illegally disposes of`
  line `the opium produced or any part thereof, shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years and shall also be liable to fine which`
  line `shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding two`
  line `lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (25122)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Punishment for contravention in relation to cannabis plant and cannabis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25122&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in`
  line `contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule or order made or condition of licence granted`
  line thereunder,--
  line
  line `(a) cultivates any cannabis plant; or`
  line
  line `(b) produces, manufactures, possesses, sells, purchases, transports, imports inter-State, exports`
  line `inter-State or uses cannabis,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `^1[(i) where such contravention relates to clause (a) with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees; and`
  line
  line `(ii) where such contravention relates to sub-clause (b),--`
  line
  line `(A) and involves small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to ^2[one year], or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(B) and involves quantity lesser than commercial quantity but greater than small quantity,`
  line `with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and with fine which`
  line `may extend to one lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(C) and involves commercial quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine`
  line `exceeding two lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 7, for sub-clauses (i) and (ii) (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 9, for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (25123)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Punishment for contravention in relation to manufactured drugs and preparations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25123&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Punishment for contravention in relation to manufactured drugs and preparations.-- Whoever, in contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule or order made or condition of licence`
  line `granted thereunder, manufactures, possesses, sells, purchases, transports, imports inter-State, exports`
  line `inter-State or uses any manufactured drug or any preparation containing any manufactured drug shall be`
  line punishable,--
  line
  line `(a) where the contravention involves small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to ^2[one year], or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the contravention involves quantity, lesser than commercial quantity but greater than`
  line `small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and with fine`
  line `which may extend to one lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) where the contravention involves commercial quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding`
  line `two lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 8, for sections 21 to 23 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 10, for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (25124)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Punishment for contravention in relation to psychotropic substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25124&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Punishment for contravention in relation to psychotropic substances.--Whoever, in`
  line `contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule or order made or condition of licence granted`
  line `thereunder, manufactures, possesses, sells, purchases, transports, imports inter-State, exports inter-State`
  line `or uses any psychotropic substance shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the contravention involves small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to ^2[one year], or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the contravention involves quantity lesser than commercial quantity but greater than`
  line `small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and with fine .`
  line
  line `(c) where the contravention involves commercial quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding`
  line `two lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 8, for sections 21 to 23 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (25125)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `Punishment for illegal import in to India, export from India or transhipment of narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25125&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1[23. Punishment for illegal import into India, export from India or transhipment of narcotic`
  line `drugs and psychotropic substances.-- Whoever, in contravention of any provision of this Act or any`
  line `rule or order made or condition of licence or permit granted or certificate or authorisation issued`
  line `thereunder, imports into India or exports from India or tranships any narcotic drug or psychotropic`
  line `substance shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the contravention involves small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to ^2[one year], or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the contravention involves quantity lesser than commercial quantity but greater than`
  line `small quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and with fine`
  line `which may extend to one lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) where the contravention involves commercial quantity, with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding`
  line `two lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 8, for sections 21 to 23 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 12, for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (25126)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Punishment for external dealings in narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances in contravention of section 12.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25126&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Whoever engages in or controls any trade whereby a narcotic drug or a`
  line `psychotropic substance is obtained outside India and supplied to any person outside India without the`
  line `previous authorisation of the Central Government or otherwise than in accordance with the condition (if`
  line `any) of such authorisation granted under section 12, shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty years and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding two`
  line `lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (25127)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 29
  title `Punishment for allowing premises, etc., to be used for commission of an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 9, for section 25 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25127&sectionno=25&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Punishment for allowing premises, etc., to be used for commission of an offence.-- Whoever, being the owner or occupier or having the control or use of any house, room, enclosure, space,`
  line `place, animal or conveyance, knowingly permits it to be used for the commission by any other person of`
  line `an offence punishable under any provision of this Act, shall be punishable with the punishment provided`
  line `for that offence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (25128)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 30
  title `Punishment for contravention of orders made under section 9A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 7 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25128&sectionno=25A&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Punishment for allowing premises, etc., to be used for commission of an offence.-- If any person`
  line `contravenes an order made under section 9A, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding one`
  line `lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (25129)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 31
  title `Punishment for certain acts by licensee or his servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25129&sectionno=26&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `If the holder of any licence, permit or`
  line `authorisation granted under this Act or any rule or order made thereunder or any person in his employ and`
  line `acting on his behalf--`
  line
  line `(a) omits, without any reasonable cause, to maintain accounts or to submit any return in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, or any rule made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) fails to produce without any reasonable cause such licence, permit or authorisation on demand`
  line `of any officer authorised by the Central Government or State Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) keeps any accounts or makes any statement which is false or which he knows or has reason to`
  line `believe to be incorrect; or`
  line
  line `(d) wilfully and knowingly does any act in breach of any of the conditions of licence, permit or`
  line `authorisation for which a penalty is not prescribed elsewhere in this Act,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with fine or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (25130)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 32
  title `Punishment for consumption of any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 10, for section 27 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25130&sectionno=27&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Punishment for consumption of any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance.-- Whoever,`
  line `consumes any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance shall be punishable,`
  line
  line `(a) where the narcotic drug or psychotropic substance consumed is cocaine, morphine, diacetylmorphine`
  line `or any other narcotic drug or any psychotropic substance as may be specified in this behalf`
  line `by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette, with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to twenty thousand rupees; or`
  line `with both; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the narcotic drug or psychotropic substance consumed is other than those specified in`
  line `or under clause (a), with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (25131)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 33
  title `Punishment for financing illicit traffic and harbouring offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25131&sectionno=27A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Punishment for financing illicit traffic and harbouring offenders.-- Whoever indulges in`
  line `financing, directly or indirectly, any, of the activities specified in sub-clauses (i) to (v) of ^2[ clause (viiib) of section 2] or harbours any person engaged in any of the aforementioned activities, shall be punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to twenty`
  line `years and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to`
  line `two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding two`
  line `lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 8 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 48 of 2021, s. 2, for “clause (viiia) of section 2” (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_b:
  sectionId (25132)
  sectionNo 27B
  orderNo 34
  title `Punishment for contravention of section 8A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25132&sectionno=27B&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_27_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[27B. Punishment for contravention of section 8A. -- Whoever contravenes the provision of`
  line `section 8A shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `years but which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (25133)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 35
  title `Punishment for attempts to commit offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25133&sectionno=28&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Whoever attempts to commit any offence`
  line `punishable under this Chapter or to cause such offence to be committed and in such attempt does any act`
  line `towards the commission of the offence shall be punishable with the punishment provided for the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (25134)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 36
  title `Punishment for abetment and criminal conspiracy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25134&sectionno=29&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever abets, or is a party to a`
  line `criminal conspiracy to commit, an offence punishable under this Chapter, shall, whether such offence be`
  line `or be not committed in consequence of such abetment or in pursuance of such criminal conspiracy, and`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in section 116 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), be punishable`
  line `with the punishment provided for the offence.`
  line
  line `(2) A person abets, or is a party to a criminal conspiracy to commit, an offence, within the meaning of`
  line `this section, who, in India, abets or is a party to the criminal conspiracy to the commission of any act in a`
  line `place without and beyond India which--`
  line
  line `(a) would constitute an offence if committed within India; or`
  line
  line `(b) under the laws of such place, is an offence relating to narcotic drugs or psychotropic`
  line `substances having all the legal conditions required to constitute it such an offence the same as or`
  line `analogous to the legal conditions required to constitute it an offence punishable under this Chapter, if`
  line `committed within India.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (25135)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 37
  title Preparation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 11, for certain words, figures and brackets (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25135&sectionno=30&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If any person makes preparation to do or omits to do anything which constitutes`
  line `an offence punishable under any of the provisions of ^1[sections 19, 24 and 27A and for offences`
  line `involving commercial quantity of any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance and from the`
  line `circumstances of the case] it may be reasonably inferred that he was determined to carry out his intention`
  line `to commit the offence but had been prevented by circumstances independent of his will, he shall be`
  line `punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one-half of the minimum`
  line `term (if any), but which may extend to one-half of the maximum term, of imprisonment with which he`
  line `would have been punishable in the event of his having committed such offence, and also with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than one-half of the minimum amount (if any), of fine with which he would have been`
  line `punishable, but which may extend to one-half of the maximum amount of fine with which he would have`
  line `ordinarily (that is to say in the absence of special reasons) been punishable, in the event aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the Judgment, impose a higher fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (25136)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 38
  title `Enhanced punishment for offences after previous conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25136&sectionno=31&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. Enhanced punishment for offences after previous conviction. -- (1) If any person who has`
  line `been convicted of the commission of, or attempt to commit, or abetment of, or criminal conspiracy to`
  line `commit, any of the offences punishable under this Act is subsequently convicted of the commission of, or`
  line `attempt to commit, or abetment of, or criminal conspiracy to commit, an offence punishable under this`
  line `Act with the same amount of punishment shall be punished for the second and every subsequent offence`
  line `with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^2[one and one-half times of the maximum`
  line `term of imprisonment, and also be liable to fine which shall extend to ^3[one and one-half times of the`
  line `maximum amount] of fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the person referred to in sub-section (1) is liable to be punished with a minimum term of`
  line `imprisonment and to a minimum amount of fine, the minimum punishment for such person shall be`
  line `^4[one and one-half times of the minimum term of imprisonment and ^5[one and one-half times of the`
  line `minimum amount] of fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose a fine exceeding the`
  line `fine for which a person is liable.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person is convicted by a competent court of criminal jurisdiction outside India under`
  line `any corresponding law, such person, in respect of such conviction, shall be dealt with for the purposes of`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) as if he had been convicted by a court in India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 31 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 14, for "one-half of the maximum term" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "one-half of the maximum amount" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "one-half of the minimum term" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "one-half of the minimum amount" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (25137)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 39
  title `Death penalty for certain offences after previous conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25137&sectionno=31A&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Death penalty for certain offences after previous conviction.-- (1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in section 31, if any person who has been convicted of the commission of, or attempt`
  line `to commit, or abetment of, or criminal conspiracy to commit, any of the offences punishable under`
  line `^2[section 19, section 24, section 27A and for offences involving commercial quantity of any narcotic drug`
  line `drug or psychotropic substance], is subsequently convicted of the commission of, or attempt to commit,`
  line `or abetment of, or criminal conspiracy to commit, an offence relating to,--`
  line
  line `(a) engaging in the production, manufacture, possession, transportation, import into India, export`
  line `from India or transhipment, of the narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances specified under column (1) of the Table below and involving the quantity which is equal to or more than the quantity`
  line `indicated against each such drug or substance, as specified in column (2) of the said Table:`
  line
  line TABLE
  line `Particulars of narcotic drugs/psychotropic substances Quantity`
  line
  line `(1) (2)`
  line `(i) Opium . . . . . . . . . . 10 kgs.`
  line
  line `(ii) Morphine . . . . . . . . . . 1 kg.`
  line
  line `(iii) Heroin . . . . . . . . . . 1 kg.`
  line
  line `(iv) Codeine . . . . . . . . . . 1 kg.`
  line
  line `(v) Thebaine . . . . . . . . . . 1 kg.`
  line
  line `(vi) Cocaine . . . . . . . . . . 500 grams.`
  line
  line `(vii) Hashish . . . . . . . . . . 20 kgs.`
  line
  line `(viii) Any mixture with or without any neutral material of any of the`
  line `above drugs`
  line `^3[lesser of the quantity`
  line `between the quantities`
  line `given against the`
  line `respective narcotic`
  line `drugs or psychotropic`
  line `substances mentioned`
  line `above forming part of`
  line `the mixture]`
  line
  line `(ix) LSD, LSD-25 (+) - N, N-Diethyllyser gamide (d-lysergic acid`
  line `diethylamide)`
  line `500 grams`
  line `(x) THC (Tetrahydrocannabinols, the following Isomers: 6a (10a),`
  line
  line `6a (7),7,8,9,10,9 (11) and their stereochemical variants)..................`
  line `500 grams`
  line
  line `(xi) Methamphetamine(+ )-2-Methylamine-l-Phenylpropane.................... 1,500 gram`
  line
  line `(xii) Methaqualone (2-Methyl-3-0-tolyl-4-(3h--)quinazolinone)...................... 1,500 gram`
  line
  line `(xiii) Amphetamine (+)-2-amino-1-phenylpropane.................... 1,500 gram`
  line
  line `(xiv) Salts and preparations of the psychotropic substances mentioned in`
  line `(ix) to (xiii)`
  line `...........................1,500 gram;`
  line
  line `(b) financing, directly or indirectly, any of the activities specified in clause (a),`
  line `^4[shall be punished with punishment which shall not be less than the punishment specified in section 31 or`
  line `or with death.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person is convicted by a competent court of criminal jurisdiction outside India under`
  line `any law corresponding to the provisions of ^5[section 19, section 24 or section 27A and for offences`
  line `involving commercial quality of any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance], such person, in respect of`
  line `such conviction, shall be dealt with for the purposes of sub-section (1) as if he had been convicted by a`
  line `court in India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 9 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 13, for "section 15 to section 25 (both inclusive) or section 27A" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 13, for "1,500 grams" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 15, for "shall be punishable with death" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 13, for certain words, figures and brackets (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (25138)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 40
  title `Punishment for offence for which no punishment is provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25138&sectionno=32&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any`
  line `provision of this Act or any rule or order made, or any condition of any licence, permit or authorisation issued thereunder for which no punishment is separately provided in this Chapter, shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (25139)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 41
  title `No suspension, remission or commutation in any sentence awarded under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 10 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25139&sectionno=32A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. No suspension, remission or commutation in any sentence awarded under this Act.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force but subject to the provisions of section 33, no sentence awarded under this`
  line `Act (other than section 27) shall be suspended or remitted or commuted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (25140)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 42
  title `Factors to be taken into account for imposing higher than the minimum punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 14 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25140&sectionno=32B&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[32B. Factors to be taken into account for imposing higher than the minimum punishment.-- Where a minimum term of imprisonment or amount of fine is prescribed for any offence committed under`
  line `this Act, the court may, in addition to such factors as it may deem fit, take into account the following`
  line `factors for imposing a punishment higher than the minimum term of imprisonment or amount of fine,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the use or threat of use of violence or arms by the offender;`
  line
  line `(b) the fact that the offender holds a public office and that he has taken advantage of that office in`
  line `committing the offence;`
  line
  line `(c) the fact that the minors are affected by the offence or the minors are used for the commission`
  line `of an offence;`
  line
  line `(d) the fact that the offence is committed in an educational institution or social service facility or`
  line `in the immediate vicinity of such institution or faculty or in other place to which school children and`
  line `students resort for educational, sports and social activities;`
  line
  line `(e) the fact that the offender belongs to organised international or any other criminal group which`
  line `is involved in the commission of the offence; and`
  line
  line `(f) the fact that the offender is involved in other illegal activities facilitated by commission of the`
  line offence.]
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (25141)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 43
  title `Application of section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 and of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25141&sectionno=33&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) or in the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958) shall apply to a person convicted of an`
  line `offence under this Act unless such person is under eighteen years of age or that the offence for which`
  line `such person is convicted is punishable under section 26 or section 27.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (25142)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 44
  title `Security for abstaining from commission of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25142&sectionno=34&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any person is convicted of`
  line `an offence punishable under any provision of Chapter IV and the court convicting him is of opinion that it`
  line `is necessary to require such person to execute a bond for abstaining from the commission of any offence`
  line `under this Act, the court may, at the time of passing sentence on such person, order him to execute a bond`
  line `for a sum proportionate to his means, with or without sureties, for abstaining from commission of any`
  line `offence under Chapter IV during such period not exceeding three years as it thinks fit to fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The bond shall be in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government and the`
  line `provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, in so far as they are applicable,`
  line `apply to all matters connected with such bond as if it were a bond to keep the peace ordered to be`
  line `executed under section 106 of that Code.`
  line
  line `(3) If the conviction is set aside on appeal or otherwise, the bond so executed shall become void.`
  line
  line `(4) An order under this section may also be made by an appellate court or by the High Court or`
  line `Sessions Judge when exercising the powers of revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (25143)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 45
  title `Presumption of culpable mental state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25143&sectionno=35&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any prosecution for an offence under this Act`
  line `which requires a culpable mental state of the accused, the court shall presume the existence of such`
  line `mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no such mental state`
  line `with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section "culpable mental state" includes intention motive, knowledge of a fact`
  line `and belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of this section , a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to exist`
  line `beyond a reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (25144)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 46
  title `Constitution of Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 11, for section 36 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25144&sectionno=36&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Constitution of Special Court.-- (1) The Government may, for the purpose of providing`
  line `speedy trial of the offences under this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute as many`
  line `Special Court as may be necessary for such area or areas as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court shall consist of a single Judge who shall be appointed by the Government with`
  line `the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this sub-section, "High Court" means the High Court of the State in which the`
  line `Sessions Judge or the Additional Sessions Judge of a Special Court was working immediately before his`
  line `appointment as such Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Judge of a Special Court unless he is,`
  line `immediately before such appointment, a Sessions Judge or an Additional Sessions Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (25145)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 47
  title `Offences triable by Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 15, for section 36A (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25145&sectionno=36A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[36A. Offences triable by Special Courts.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),`
  line
  line `(a) all offences under this Act which are punishable with imprisonment for a term of more than`
  line `three years shall be triable only by the Special Court constituted for the area in which the offence has`
  line `been committed or where there are more Special Courts than one for such area, by such one of them`
  line `as may be specified in this behalf by the Government;`
  line
  line `(b) where a person accused of or suspected of the commission of an offence under this Act is`
  line `forwarded to a Magistrate under sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A) of section 167 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), such Magistrate may authorise the detention of such person in`
  line `such custody as he thinks fit for a period not exceeding fifteen days in the whole where such`
  line `Magistrate is a Judicial Magistrate and seven days in the whole where such Magistrate is an`
  line `Executive Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases which are triable by the Special Court where such Magistrate considers`
  line
  line `(i) when such person is forwarded to him as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(ii) upon or at any time before the expiry of the period of detention authorised by him,`
  line
  line `that the detention of such person is unnecessary, he shall order such person to be forwarded to the`
  line `Special Court having jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) the Special Court may exercise, in relation to the person forwarded to it under clause (b), the`
  line `same power which a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try a case may exercise under section 167 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), in relation to an accused person in such case who`
  line `has been forwarded to him under that section;`
  line
  line `(d) a Special Court may, upon perusal of police report of the facts constituting an offence under`
  line `this Act or upon complaint made by an officer of the Central Government or a State Government`
  line `authorised in his behalf, take cognizance of that offence without the accused being committed to it for`
  line trial.
  line
  line `(2) When trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court may also try an offence other than an`
  line `offence under this Act with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High Court`
  line `regarding bail under section 439 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), and the High Court`
  line `may exercise such powers including the power under cluase (b) of sub-section (1) of that section as if the`
  line `reference to "Magistrate" in that section included also a reference to a Special Court constituted under`
  line `section 36.`
  line
  line `(4) In respect of persons accused of an offence punishable under section 19 or section 24 or section`
  line `27A or for offences involving commercial quantity the references in sub-section (2) of section 167 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) thereof to "ninety days", where they occur, shall be`
  line `construed as reference to "one hundred and eighty days":`
  line
  line `Provided that, if it is not possible to complete the investigation within the said period of one hundred`
  line `and eighty days, the Special Court may extend the said period up to one year on the report of the Public`
  line `Prosecutor indicating the progress of the investigation and the specific reasons for the detention of the`
  line `accused beyond the said period of one hundred and eighty days.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `offences punishable under this Act with imprisonment for a term of not more than three years may be`
  line `tried summarily.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_b:
  sectionId (25146)
  sectionNo 36B
  orderNo 48
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25146&sectionno=36B&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content:
  string
  line `36B. Appeal and revision.-- The High Court may exercise, so for as may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36_c:
  sectionId (25147)
  sectionNo 36C
  orderNo 49
  title `Application of Code to proceedings before a Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25147&sectionno=36C&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_36_c_content:
  string
  line `36C. Application of Code to proceedings before a Special Court.-- Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), (including the provisions as`
  line `to bail and bonds) shall apply to the proceedings before a Special Court and for the purposes of the said`
  line `provisions, the Special Court shall be deemed to be a Court of Session and the person conducting a`
  line `prosecution before a Special Court, shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36_d:
  sectionId (25148)
  sectionNo 36D
  orderNo 50
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_d_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 16, for section 36D (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25148&sectionno=36D&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_36_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[36D. Transitional provisions.-- (1) Any offence committed under this Act on or after the`
  line `commencement of the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances (Amendment) Act, 1988 (2 of 1989),`
  line `which is triable by a Special Court shall, until a Special Court is constituted under section 36,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be tried by a`
  line `Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any proceedings in relation to any offence committed under this Act on or after the`
  line `commencement of the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances (Amendment) Act, 1988 (2 of 1989)`
  line `are pending before a Court of Session, then, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), such`
  line `proceeding shall be heard and disposed of by the Court of Session:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall affect the power of the High Court under`
  line `section 407 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) to transfer any case or class of cases`
  line `taken cognizance by a Court of Session under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (25149)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 51
  title `Offences to be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25149&sectionno=37&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[37. Offences to be cognizable and non-bailable. -- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(a) every offence punishable under this Act shall be cognizable;`
  line
  line `(b) no person accused of an offence punishable for ^1[offences under section 19 or section 24 or`
  line `section 27A and also for offences involving commercial quantity] shall be released on bail or on his`
  line `own bond unless--`
  line
  line `(i) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release, and`
  line
  line `(ii) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) The limitations on granting of bail specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) are in addition to the`
  line `limitations under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force on granting of bail.].`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 12, for section 37 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 17, for "a term of imprisonment of five years or more under this Act" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (25150)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 52
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25150&sectionno=38&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under Chapter IV has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person, who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under Chapter IV has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (25151)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power of court to release certain offenders on probation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 18 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25151&sectionno=39&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any addict is found guilty`
  line `of an offence punishable under section 27 ^1[or for offences relating to small quantity of any narcotic drug`
  line `or psychotropic substance] and if the court by which he is found guilty is of the opinion, regard being had`
  line `to the age, character, antecedents or physical or mental condition of the offender, that it is expedient so to`
  line `do, then, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `court may, instead of sentencing him at once to any imprisonment, with his consent, direct that he be`
  line `released for undergoing medical treatment for de-toxification or de-addiction from a hospital or an`
  line `institution maintained or recognised by Government and on his entering into a bond in the form`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, with or without sureties, to appear and furnish before the court`
  line `within a period not exceeding one year, a report regarding the result of his medical treatment and, in the`
  line `meantime, to abstain from the commission of any offence under Chapter IV.`
  line
  line `(2) If it appears to the court, having regard to the report regarding the result of the medical treatment`
  line `furnished under sub-section (1), that it is expedient so to do, the court may direct the release of the`
  line `offender after due admonition on his entering into a bond in the form prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government, with or without sureties, for abstaining from the commission of any offence under`
  line `Chapter IV during such period not exceeding three years as the court may deem fit to specify or on his`
  line `failure so to abstain, to appear before the court and receive sentence when called upon during such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (25152)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power of court to publish names, place of business, etc., of certain offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25152&sectionno=40&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `person is convicted of any of the offences punishable under section 15 to section 25 (both inclusive),`
  line `section 28, section 29 or section 30, it shall be competent for the court convicting the person to cause the`
  line `name and place of business or residence of such person, nature of the contravention, the fact that the`
  line `person has been so convicted and such other particulars as the court may consider to be appropriate in the`
  line `circumstances of the case, to be published at the expense of such person in such newspapers or in such`
  line `manner as the court may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) No publication under sub-section (1) shall be made until the period for preferring an appeal`
  line `against the orders of the court has expired without any appeal having been preferred, or such appeal,`
  line `having been preferred, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses of any publication under sub-section (1) shall be recoverable from the convicted`
  line `person as if it were a fine imposed by the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (25153)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to issue warrant and authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 19, for sections 41 to 43 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25153&sectionno=41&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^1[41. Power to issue warrant and authorisation.-- (l) A Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate of`
  line `the first class or any Magistrate of the second class specially empowered by the State Government in this`
  line `behalf, may issue a warrant for the arrest of any person whom he has reason to believe to have committed`
  line `any offence punishable under this Act, or for the search, whether by day or by night, of any building,`
  line `conveyance or place in which he has reason to believe any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance or`
  line `controlled substance in respect of which an offence punishable under this Act has been committed or any`
  line `document or other article which may furnish evidence of the commission of such offence or any illegally`
  line `acquired property or any document or other article which may furnish evidence of holding any illegally`
  line `acquired property which is liable for seizure or freezing or forfeiture under Chapter VA of this Act is kept`
  line `or concealed:`
  line
  line `(2) Any such officer of gazetted rank of the departments of central excise, narcotics, customs, revenue`
  line `intelligence or any other department of the Central Government including the para-military forces or the`
  line `armed forces as is empowered in this behalf by general or special order by the Central Government, or`
  line `any such officer of the revenue, drugs control, excise, police or any other department of a State`
  line `Government as is empowered in this behalf by general or special order of the State Government if he has`
  line `reason to believe from personal knowledge or information given by any person and taken in writing that`
  line `any person has committed an offence punishable under this Act or that any narcotic drug or psychotropic`
  line `substance or controlled substance in respect of which any offence under this Act has been committed or`
  line `any document or other article which may furnish evidence of the commission of such offence or any`
  line `illegally acquired property or any document or other article which may furnish evidence of holding any`
  line `illegally acquired property which is liable for seizure or freezing or forfeiture under Chapter VA of this`
  line `Act is kept or concealed in any building, conveyance or place, may authorise any officer subordinate to`
  line `him but superior in rank to a peon, sepoy or a constable to arrest such a person or search a building,`
  line `conveyance or place whether by day or by night or himself arrest such a person or search a building,`
  line `conveyance or place.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer to whom a warrant under sub-section (1) is addressed and the officer who authorised`
  line `the arrest or search or the officer who is so authorised under sub-section (2) shall have all the powers of`
  line `an officer acting under section 42.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (25154)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of entry, search, seizure and arrest without warrant or authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25154&sectionno=42&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^[42. Power of entry, search, seizure and arrest without warrant or authorisation.-- (l) Any such`
  line `officer (being an officer superior in rank to a peon, sepoy or constable) of the departments of central`
  line `excise, narcotics, customs, revenue intellegence or any other department of the Central Government`
  line `including para-military forces or armed forces as is empowered in this behalf by general or special order`
  line `by the Central Government, or any such officer (being an officer superior in rank to a peon, sepoy or`
  line `constable) of the revenue, drugs control, excise, police or any other department of a State Government as`
  line `is empowered in this behalf by general or special order of the State Government, if he has reason to`
  line `believe from personal knowledge or information given by any person and taken down in writing that any`
  line `narcotic drug, or psychotropic substance, or controlled substance in respect of which an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act has been committed or any document or other article which may furnish`
  line `evidence of the commission of such offence or any illegally acquired property or any document or other`
  line `article which may furnish evidence of holding any illegally acquired property which is liable for seizure`
  line `or freezing or forfeiture under Chapter VA of this Act is kept or concealed in any building, conveyance or`
  line `enclosed place, may between sunrise and sunset,-`
  line
  line `(a) enter into and search any such building, conveyance or place;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of resistance, break open any door and remove any obstacle to such entry;`
  line
  line `(c) seize such drug or substance and all materials used in the manufacture thereof and any other`
  line `article and any animal or conveyance which he has reason to believe to be liable to confiscation under`
  line `this Act and any document or other article which he has reason to believe may furnish evidence of the`
  line `commission of any offence punishable under this Act or furnish evidence of holding any illegally`
  line `acquired property which is liable for seizure or freezing or forfeiture under Chapter VA of this Act;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) detain and search, and, if he thinks proper, arrest any person whom he has reason to believe to`
  line `have committed any offence punishable under this Act:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that in respect of holder of a licence for manufacture of manufactured drugs or`
  line `psychotropic substances or controlled substances granted under this Act or any rule or order made`
  line `thereunder, such power shall be exercised by an officer not below the rank of sub-inspector:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] if such officer has reason to believe that a search warrant or authorisation`
  line `cannot be obtained without affording opportunity for the concealment of evidence or facility for the`
  line `escape of an offender, he may enter and search such building, conveyance or enclosed place at any`
  line `time between sunset and sunrise after recording the grounds of his belief.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an officer takes down any information in writing under sub-section (1) or records grounds`
  line `for his belief under the proviso thereto, he shall within seventy-two hours send a copy thereof to his`
  line `immediate official superior.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 19, for sections 41 to 43 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 16, for "Provided that"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (25155)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of seizure and arrest in public place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 19, for sections 41 to 43 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25155&sectionno=43&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[43. Power of seizure and arrest in public place. -- Any officer of any of the departments mentioned`
  line `in section 42 may`
  line
  line `(a) seize in any public place or in transit, any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance or`
  line `controlled substance in respect of which he has reason to believe an offence punishable under this Act`
  line `has been committed, and, along with such drug or substance, any animal or conveyance or article`
  line `liable to confiscation under this Act, any document or other article which he has reason to believe`
  line `may furnish evidence of the commission of an offence punishable under this Act or any document or`
  line `other article which may furnish evidence of holding any illegally acquired property which is liable for`
  line `seizure or freezing or forfeiture under Chapter VA of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) detain and search any person whom he has reason to believe to have committed an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act, and if such person has any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance or`
  line `controlled substance in his possession and such possession appears to him to be unlawful, arrest him`
  line `and any other person in his company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "public place" includes any public`
  line `conveyance, hotel, shop, or other place intended for use by, or accessible to, the public.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (25156)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power of entry, search, seizure and arrest in offences relating to coca plant, opium poppy and cannabis plant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 20 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25156&sectionno=44&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 41, 42 and 43, shall so far as may be, apply in relation`
  line `to the offence punishable under Chapter IV and relating to coca plant, the opium poppy or cannabis plant`
  line `and for this purpose references in those sections to narcotic drugs, or psychotropic substance ^1[or`
  line `controlled substance], shall be construed as including references to coca plant, the opium poppy and`
  line `cannabis plant.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (25157)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 59
  title `Procedure where seizure of goods liable to confiscation not practicable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25157&sectionno=45&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where it is not`
  line `practicable to seize any goods (including standing crop) which are liable to confiscation under this Act,`
  line `any officer duly authorised under section 42 may serve on the owner or person in possession of the goods,`
  line `an order that he shall not remove, part with or otherwise deal with the goods except with the previous`
  line `permission of such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (25158)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 60
  title `Duty of land holder to give information of illegal cultivation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25158&sectionno=46&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Every holder of land shall give`
  line `immediate information to any officer of the Police or of any of the departments mentioned in section 42`
  line `of all the opium poppy, cannabis plant or coca plant which may be illegally cultivated within his land and`
  line `every such holder of land who knowingly neglects to give such information, shall be liable to punishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (25159)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 61
  title `Duty of certain officers to give information of illegal cultivation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25159&sectionno=47&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Every officer of the`
  line `Government and every panch, sarpanch and other village officer of whatever description shall give`
  line `immediate information to any officer of the Police or of any of the departments mentioned in section 42`
  line `when it may come to his knowledge that any land has been illegally cultivated with the opium poppy,`
  line `cannabis plant or coca plant, and every such officer of the Government, panch, sarpanch and other village`
  line `officer who neglects to give such information shall be liable to punishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (25160)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power of attachment of crop illegally cultivated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 13 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25160&sectionno=48&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Any Metropolitan Magistrate, Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class or any Magistrate specially empowered in this behalf by the State`
  line `Government ^1[or any officer of a gazetted rank empowered under section 42] may order attachment of`
  line `any opium poppy, cannabis plant or coca plant which he has reason to believe to have been illegally`
  line `cultivated and while doing so may pass such order (including an order to destroy the crop) as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (25161)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 63
  title `Power to stop and search conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 21 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25161&sectionno=49&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Any officer authorised under section 42, may, if he has`
  line `reason to suspect that any animal or conveyance is, or is about to be, used for the transport of any narcotic`
  line `drug or psychotropic substance ^1[or controlled substance], in respect of which he suspects that any`
  line `provision of this Act has been, or is being, or is about to be, contravened at any time, stop such animal or`
  line `conveyance, or, in the case of an aircraft, compel it to land and--`
  line
  line `(a) rummage and search the conveyance or part thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) examine and search any goods on the animal or in the conveyance;`
  line
  line `(c) if it becomes necessary to stop the animal or the conveyance, he may use all lawful means for`
  line `stopping it, and where such means fail, the animal or the conveyance may be fired upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (25162)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 64
  title `Conditions under which search of persons shall be conducted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25162&sectionno=50&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any officer duly`
  line `authorised under section 42 is about to search any person under the provisions of section 41, section 42 or`
  line `section 43, he shall, if such person so requires, take such person without unnecessary delay to nearest`
  line `Gazetted Officer of any of the departments mentioned in section 42 or to the nearest Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) If such requisition is made, the officer may detain the person until he can bring him before the`
  line `Gazetted Officer or the Magistrate referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Gazetted Officer or the Magistrate before whom any such person is brought shall, if he sees`
  line `no reasonable ground for search, forthwith discharge the person but otherwise shall direct that search be`
  line made.
  line
  line `(4) No female shall be searched by anyone excepting a female.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) When an officer duly authorised under section 42 has reason to believe that it is not possible to`
  line `take the person to be searched to the nearest Gazetted Officer or Magistrate without the possibility of the`
  line `person to be searched parting with possession of any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance, or`
  line `controlled substance or article or document, he may, instead of taking such person to the nearest Gazetted`
  line `Officer or Magistrate, proceed to search the person as provided under section100 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(6) After a search is conducted under sub-section (5), the officer shall record the reasons for such`
  line `belief which necessitated such search and within seventy-two hours send a copy thereof to his immediate`
  line `official superior.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_a:
  sectionId (25163)
  sectionNo 50A
  orderNo 65
  title `Power to undertake controlled delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 23 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25163&sectionno=50A&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_50_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[50A. Power to undertake controlled delivery.-- The Director General of Narcotics Control`
  line `Bureau constituted under sub-section (3) of section 4 or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf,`
  line `may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, undertake controlled delivery of any consignment`
  line to--
  line
  line `(a) any destination in India;`
  line
  line `(b) a foreign country, in consultation with the competent authority of such foreign country to`
  line `which such consignment is destined, in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (25164)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 66
  title `Provisions of the code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to apply to warrants, arrests, searches and seizures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25164&sectionno=51&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply, in so far`
  line `as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, to all warrants issued and arrests, searches and`
  line `seizures made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (25165)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 67
  title `Disposal of persons arrested and articles seized.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25165&sectionno=52&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any officer arresting a person under`
  line `section 41, section 42, section 43 or section 44 shall, as soon as may be, inform him of the grounds for`
  line `such arrest.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person arrested and article seized under warrant issued under sub-section (1) of section 41`
  line `shall be forwarded without unnecessary delay to the Magistrate by whom the warrant was issued.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person arrested and article seized under sub-section (2) of section 41, section 42, section 43`
  line `or section 44 shall be forwarded without unnecessary delay to--`
  line
  line `(a) the officer-in-charge of the nearest police station, or`
  line
  line `(b) the officer empowered under section 53.`
  line
  line `(4) The authority or officer to whom any person or article is forwarded under sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3) shall, with all convenient despatch, take such measures as may be necessary for the`
  line `disposal according to law of such person or article.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52_a:
  sectionId (25166)
  sectionNo 52A
  orderNo 68
  title `Disposal of seized narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25166&sectionno=52A&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[52A. Disposal of seized narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances.-- ^2[(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, having regard to the hazardous nature, vulnerability to theft, substitution, constraint of`
  line `proper storage space or any other relevant consideration, in respect of any narcotic drugs, psychotropic`
  line `substances, controlled substances or conveyances, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify such`
  line `narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances, controlled substances or conveyance or class of narcotic drugs,`
  line `class of psychotropic substances, class of controlled substances or conveyances, which shall, as soon as`
  line `may be after their seizure, be disposed of by such officer and in such manner as that Government may,`
  line `from time to time, determine after following the procedure hereinafter specified.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where any ^3[narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances, controlled substances or conveyances] has`
  line `been seized and forwarded to the officer-in-charge of the nearest police station or to the officer`
  line `empowered under section 53, the officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall prepare an inventory of such`
  line `^3[narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances, controlled substances or conveyances] containing such details`
  line `relating to their description, quality, quantity, mode of packing, marks, numbers or such other identifying`
  line `particulars of the ^3[narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances, controlled substances] or conveyances or the`
  line `packing in which they are packed, country of origin and other particulars as the officer referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) may consider relevant to the identity of the ^3[narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances,`
  line `controlled substances or conveyances] in any proceedings under this Act and make an application, to any`
  line `Magistrate for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(a) certifying the correctness of the inventory so prepared; or`
  line
  line `(b) taking, in the presence of such magistrate, photographs of ^4[such drugs, substances or`
  line `conveyances] and certifying such photographs as true; or`
  line
  line `(c) allowing to draw representative samples of such drugs or substances, in the presence of such`
  line `magistrate and certifying the correctness of any list of samples so drawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is made under sub-section (2), the Magistrate shall, as soon as may be, allow`
  line `the application.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1972) or the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every court trying an offence under this Act, shall treat the`
  line `innventory, the photographs of ^5[narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances, controlled substances or`
  line `conveyances] and any list of samples drawn under sub-section (2) and certified by the Magistrate, as`
  line `primary evidence in respect of such offence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 14 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 17, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "narcotic drug or psychotropic substance" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "such drugs or substances" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s.17, for "narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (25167)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to invest officers of certain departments with powers of an officer-in-charge of a police station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25167&sectionno=53&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, after consultation with the State Government, may, by`
  line `notification published in the Official Gazette, invest any officer of the department of central excise,`
  line `narcotics, customs, revenue intelligence ^1[or any other department of the Central Government including`
  line `para-military forces or armed forces or any class of such officers] with the powers of an officer-in-charge`
  line `of a police station for the investigation of the offences under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification published in the Official Gazette, invest any officer of`
  line `the department of drugs control, revenue or excise ^2[or any other department] or any class of such officers`
  line `with the powers of an officer-in-charge of a police station for the investigation of offences under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 24, for "or Border Security Force" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_a:
  sectionId (25168)
  sectionNo 53A
  orderNo 70
  title `Relevancy of statements under certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 15 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25168&sectionno=53A&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[53A. Relevancy of statements under certain circumstances.-- (1) A statement made and signed`
  line `by a person before any officer empowered under section 53 for the investigation of offences, during the`
  line `course of any inquiry or proceedings by such officer, shall be relevant for the purpose of proving, in any`
  line `prosecution for an offence under this Act, the truth of the facts which it contains,`
  line
  line `(a) when the person who made the statement is dead or connot be found, or is incapable of giving`
  line `evidence, or is kept out of the way by the adverse party, or whose presence cannot be obtained`
  line `without an amount of delay or expense which, under the circumstances of the case, the court`
  line `considers unreasonable; or`
  line
  line `(b) when the person who made the statement is examined as a witness in the case before the court`
  line `and the court is of the opinion that, having regard to the circumstances of the case, the statement`
  line `should be admitted in evidence in the interest of justice.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to any proceedings`
  line `under this Act or the rules or orders made thereunder, other than a proceeding before a court, as they`
  line `apply in relation to a proceeding before a court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (25169)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 71
  title `Presumption from possession of illicit articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 25, for section 54 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25169&sectionno=54&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `^1[54. Presumption from possession of illicit articles.-- In trials under this Act, it may be presumed,`
  line `unless and until the contrary is proved, that the accused has committed an offence under this Act in`
  line `respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance or controlled substance;`
  line
  line `(b) any opium poppy, cannabis plant or coca plant growing on any land which he has cultivated;`
  line
  line `(c) any apparatus specially designed or any group of utensils specially adopted for the`
  line `manufacture of any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance or controlled substance; or`
  line
  line `(d) any materials which have undergone any process towards the manufacture of a narcotic drug`
  line `or psychotropic substance or controlled substance, or any residue left of the materials from which any`
  line `narcotic drug or psychotropic substance or controlled substance has been manufactured,`
  line
  line `for the possession of which he fails to account satisfactorily.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (25170)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 72
  title `Police to take charge of articles seized and delivered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25170&sectionno=55&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `An officer-in-charge of a police station`
  line `shall take charge of and keep in safe custody, pending the orders of the Magistrate, all articles seized under this Act within the local area of that police station and which may be delivered to him, and shall`
  line `allow any officer who may accompany such articles to the police station or who may be deputed for the`
  line `purpose, to affix his seal to such articles or to take samples of and from them and all samples so taken`
  line `shall also be sealed with a seal of the officer-in-charge of the police station.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (25171)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 73
  title `Obligation of officers to assist each other.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25171&sectionno=56&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `All officers of the several departments mentioned`
  line `in section 42 shall, upon notice given or request made, be legally bound to assist each other in carrying`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (25172)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 74
  title `Report of arrest and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25172&sectionno=57&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person makes any arrest or seizure under this Act,`
  line `he shall, within forty-eight hours next after such arrest or seizure, make a full report of all the particulars`
  line `of such arrest or seizure to his immediate official superior.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57_a:
  sectionId (25173)
  sectionNo 57A
  orderNo 75
  title `Report of seizure of property of the person arrested by the notified officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25173&sectionno=57A&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_57_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[57A. Report of seizure of property of the person arrested by the notified officer.--Whenever`
  line `any officer notified under section 53 makes an arrest or seizure under this Act, and the provisions of`
  line `Chapter VA apply to any person involved in the case of such arrest or seizure, the officer shall make a`
  line `report of the illegally acquired properties of such person to the jurisdictional competent authority within`
  line `ninety days of the arrest or seizure.]`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (25174)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 76
  title `Punishment for vexatious entry, search, seizure or arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25174&sectionno=58&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person empowered under`
  line `section 42 or section 43 or section 44 who--`
  line
  line `(a) without reasonable ground of suspicion enters or searches, or causes to be entered or searched,`
  line `any building, conveyance or place;`
  line
  line `(b) vexatiously and unnecessarily seizes the property of any person on the pretence of seizing or`
  line `searching for any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance or other article liable to be confiscated`
  line `under this Act, or of seizing any document or other article liable to be seized under section 42, section`
  line `43 or section 44; or`
  line
  line `(c) vexatiously and unnecessarily detains, searches or arrests any person,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person wilfully and maliciously giving false information and so causing an arrest or a search`
  line `being made under this Act shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (25175)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 77
  title `Failure of officer in duty or his connivance at the contravention of the provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 16, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25175&sectionno=59&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any officer, on whom any duty has been imposed by or under this Act and who ceases or`
  line `refuses to perform or withdraws himself from the duties of his office shall, unless he has obtained the`
  line `express written permission of his official superior or has other lawful excuse for so doing, be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Any officer on whom any duty has been imposed by or under this Act or any person who has`
  line `been given the custody of--`
  line
  line `(a) any addict; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other person who has been charged with an offence under this Act,`
  line
  line `and who wilfully aids in, or connives at, the contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule or`
  line `order made thereunder, shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than ten years but which may extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be`
  line `less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "officer" includes any person`
  line `employed in a hospital or institution maintained or recognised by the Government or a local authority`
  line `under section 64A for providing de-addiction treatment.]`
  line
  line `(3) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) except on a`
  line `complaint in writing made with the previous sanction of the Central Government, or as the case may be,`
  line `the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (25176)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 78
  title `Liability of illicit drugs, substances, plants, articles and conveyances to confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25176&sectionno=60&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)`
  line `Whenever any offence punishable under this Act has been committed, the narcotic drug, psychotropic`
  line `substance, controlled substance, opium poppy, coca plant, cannabis plant, materials, apparatus and`
  line `utensils in respect of which or by means of which such offence has been committed, shall be liable to`
  line confiscation.]
  line
  line `(2) Any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance ^2[or controlled substances] lawfully produced,`
  line `imported inter-State, exported inter-State, imported into India, transported, manufactured, possessed,`
  line `used, purchased or sold along with, or in addition to, any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance ^2[or`
  line `controlled substances] which is liable to confiscation under sub-section (1) and the receptacles, packages`
  line `and coverings in which any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance ^2[or controlled substances], materials,`
  line `apparatus or utensils liable to confiscation under sub-section (1) is found, and the other contents, if any, of`
  line `such receptacles or packages shall likewise be liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `(3) Any animal or conveyance used in carrying any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance ^2[or`
  line `controlled substances], or any article liable to confiscation under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall`
  line `be liable to confiscation, unless the owner of the animal or conveyance proves that it was so used without`
  line `the knowledge or connivance of the owner himself, his agent, if any, and the person-in-charge of the`
  line `animal or conveyance and that each of them had taken all reasonable precautions against such use.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 26, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (25177)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 79
  title `Confiscation of goods used for concealing illicit drugs or substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for "narcotic drug or psychotropic substance" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25177&sectionno=61&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Any goods used for`
  line `concealing any ^1[narcotic drug, psychotropic substance] or controlled substance which is liable to`
  line `confiscation under this Act shall also be liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section "goods" does not include conveyance as a means of transport.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (25178)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 80
  title `Confiscation of sale proceeds of illicit drugs or substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for "narcotic drug or psychotropic substance" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25178&sectionno=62&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Where any ^1[narcotic drug,`
  line `psychotropic substance] or controlled substance is sold by a person having knowledge or reason to`
  line `believe that the drug or substance is liable to confiscation under this Act, the sale proceeds thereof shall`
  line `also be liable to confiscation.`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (25179)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 81
  title `Procedure in making confiscations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25179&sectionno=63&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the trial of offences under this Act, whether the`
  line `accused is convicted or acquitted or discharged, the court shall decide whether any article or thing seized`
  line `under this Act is liable to confiscation under section 60 or section 61 or section 62 and, if it decides that`
  line `the article is so liable, it may order confiscation accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any article or thing seized under this Act appears to be liable to confiscation under section`
  line `60 or section 61 or section 62, but the person who committed the offence in connection therewith is not`
  line `known or cannot be found, the court may inquire into and decide such liability, and may order`
  line `confiscation accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of confiscation of an article or thing shall be made until the expiry of one`
  line `month from the date of seizure, or without hearing any person who may claim any right thereto and the`
  line `evidence, if any, which he produces in respect of his claim:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if any such article or thing, other than a narcotic drug, psychotropic substance`
  line `^1[controlled substance], the opium poppy, coca plant or cannabis plant is liable to speedy and natural`
  line `decay, or if the court is of opinion that its sale would be for the benefit of its owner, it may at any time`
  line `direct it to be sold; and the provisions of this sub-section shall, as nearly as may be practicable, apply to`
  line `the net proceeds of the sale.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 9 of 2001, s. 29 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (25180)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 82
  title `Power to tender immunity from prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25180&sectionno=64&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or the State`
  line `Government may, if it is of opinion (the reasons for such opinion being recorded in writing) that with a`
  line `view to obtaining the evidence of any person appearing to have been directly or indirectly concerned in or`
  line `privy to the contravention of any of provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made thereunder it is`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do, tender to such person immunity from prosecution for any offence under`
  line `this Act or under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any other Central Act or State Act, as the`
  line `case may be, for the time being in force, on condition of his making a full and true disclosure of the whole`
  line `circumstances relating to such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) A tender of immunity made to, and accepted by, the person concerned, shall, to the extent to`
  line `which the immunity extends, render him immune from prosecution for any offence in respect of which`
  line `the tender was made.`
  line
  line `(3) If it appears to the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government, that any`
  line `person to whom immunity has been tendered under this section has not complied with the conditions on`
  line `which the tender was made or is wilfully concealing anything or is giving false evidence, the Central`
  line `Government or, as the case may be, the State Government, may record a finding to that effect and`
  line `thereupon the immunity shall be deemed to have been withdrawn and such person may be tried for the`
  line `offence in respect of which the tender of immunity was made or for any other offence of which he`
  line `appears to have been guilty in connection with the same matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64_a:
  sectionId (25181)
  sectionNo 64A
  orderNo 83
  title `Immunity from prosecution to addicts volunteering for treatment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for section 64A (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25181&sectionno=64A&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_64_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[64A. Immunity from prosecution to addicts volunteering for treatment.-- Any addict, who is`
  line `charged with an offence punishable under section 27 or with offences involving small quantity of narcotic`
  line `drugs or psychotropic substances, who voluntarily seeks to undergo medical treatment for de-addiction`
  line `from a hospital or an institution maintained or recognised by the Government or a local authority and`
  line `undergoes such treatment shall not be liable to prosecution under section 27 or under any other section for`
  line `offences involving small quantity of narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said immunity from prosecution may be withdrawn if the addict does not undergo`
  line `the complete treatment for de-addiction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (25182)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 84
  title [Omitted].
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25182&sectionno=65&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `[Power to make rules regulating disposal of confiscated articles and rewards].-- Omitted by the`
  line `Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances (Amendment) Act, 1989 (2 of 1989), s. 18`
  line `(w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (25183)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 85
  title `Presumption as to documents in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25183&sectionno=66&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Where any document--`
  line
  line `(i) is produced or furnished by any person or has been seized from the custody or control of any`
  line `person, in either case, under this Act or under any other law, or`
  line
  line `(ii) has been received from any place outside India (duly authenticated by such authority or`
  line `person and in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government) in the course of`
  line `investigation of any offence under this Act alleged to have been committed by a person,`
  line
  line `and such document is tendered in any prosecution under this Act in evidence against him, or against him`
  line `and any other person who is tried jointly with him, the court shall--`
  line
  line `(a) presume, unless the contrary is proved, that the signature and every other part of such`
  line `document which purports to be in the handwriting of any particular person or which the court may`
  line `reason ably assume to have been signed by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, is in`
  line `that persons handwriting; and in the case of a document executed or attested, that it was executed or`
  line `attested by the person by whom it purports to have been so executed or attested;`
  line
  line `(b) admit the document in evidence, notwithstanding that it is not duly stamped, if such document`
  line `is otherwise admissible in evidence;`
  line
  line `(c) examine any person acquainted with the facts and circumcontrary is proved, the truth of the`
  line `contents of such document.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (25184)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power to call for information, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25184&sectionno=67&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Any officer referred to in section 42 who is authorised in`
  line `this behalf by the Central Government or a State Government may, during the course of any enquiry in`
  line `connection with the contravention of any provision of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) call for information from any person for the purpose of satisfying himself whether there has`
  line `been any contravention of the provisions of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) require any person to produce or deliver any document or thing useful or relevant to the`
  line enquiry;
  line
  line `(c) examine any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (25185)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 87
  title `Information as to commission of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25185&sectionno=68&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `No officer acting in exercise of powers vested in`
  line `him under any provision of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder shall be compelled to say`
  line `whence he got any information as to the commission of any offence`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68_a:
  sectionId (25186)
  sectionNo 68A
  orderNo 88
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25186&sectionno=68A&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content:
  string
  line `^1, ^2[68A. Application.-- (1) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply only to the persons specified in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The persons referred to in sub-section (1) are the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) every person who has been convicted of an offence punishable under this Act with`
  line `imprisonment for a term of ^3[ten] years or more;`
  line
  line `(b) every person who has been convicted of a similar offence by a competent court of criminal`
  line `jurisdiction outside India;`
  line
  line `(c) every person in respect of whom an order of detention has been made under the Prevention of`
  line `IIicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1988 (46 of 1988), or under the`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir Prevention of IIicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act,`
  line 1988;
  line
  line `^4[(cc) every person who has been arrested or against whom a warrant or authorisation of arrest`
  line `has been issued for the commission of an offence punishable under this Act with imprisonment for a`
  line `term of ten years or more, and every person who has been arrested or against whom a warrant or`
  line `authorisation of arrest has been issued for the commission of a similar offence under any`
  line `corresponding law of any other country.]`
  line
  line `Provided that such order of detention has not been revoked on the report of the Advisory Board`
  line `constituted under the said Acts or such order of detention has not been set aside by a court of`
  line `competent jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(d) every person who is a relative of a person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c)`
  line `^4[or clause (cc);]`
  line
  line `(e) every associate of a person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c)`
  line `^4[or clause (cc);]`
  line
  line `(f) any holder (hereafter in this clause referred to as the present holder) of any property which`
  line `was at any time previously held by a person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c)`
  line ^4[or
  line `clause (cc);] unless the present holder or, as the case may be, any one who held such property after`
  line `such person and before the present holder, is or was a transferee in good faith for adequate`
  line consideration.]
obj_root_law_sections_68_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 19, for "FORFEITURE OF PROPERTY DERIVED FROM, OR USED, IN ILLICIT TRAFFIC"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 31, for "five" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 31, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_b:
  sectionId (25187)
  sectionNo 68B
  orderNo 89
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25187&sectionno=68B&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[68B. Definitions. -- In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate Tribunal ^2[referred to in] section 68N;`
  line
  line `(b) "associate" in relation to a person whose property is liable to be forfeited under this Chapter,`
  line means--
  line
  line `(i) any individual who had been or is residing in the residential premises (including`
  line `out-houses) of such person;`
  line
  line `(ii) any individual who had been or is managing the affairs or keeping the accounts of such`
  line person;
  line
  line `(iii) any association of persons, body of individuals, partnership firm, or private company`
  line `within the meaning of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), of which such person had been or is`
  line `a member, partner or director;`
  line
  line `(iv) any individual who had been or is a member, partner or director of an association of`
  line `persons, body of individuals, partnership firm or private company referred to in sub-clause (iii) at`
  line `any time when such person had been or is a member, partner or director of such association,`
  line `body, partnership firm or private company;`
  line
  line `(v) any person, who had been or is managing the affairs, or keeping the accounts, of any`
  line `association of persons, body of individuals, partnership firm or private company referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (iii);`
  line
  line `(vi) the trustee of any trust, where,--`
  line
  line `(1) the trust has been created by such person; or`
  line
  line `(2) the value of the assets contributed by such person (including the value of the assets, if`
  line `any, contributed by him earlier) to the trust amounts, on the date on which contribution is`
  line `made, to not less than twenty per cent. of the value of the assets of the trust on that date;`
  line
  line `(vii) where the competent authority, for reasons to be recorded in writing, considers that any`
  line `properties of such person are held on his behalf by any other person, such other person;`
  line
  line `(c) "competent authority" means an officer of the Central Government authorised by it under`
  line `section 68D;`
  line
  line `(d) concealment means the concealment or disguise of the nature, source, disposition,`
  line `movement or ownership of property and includes the movement or conversion of such property by`
  line `electronic transmission or by any other means;`
  line
  line `(e) "freezing" means temporarily prohibiting the transfer, conversion, disposition or movement of`
  line `property by an order issued under section 68F;`
  line
  line `(f) "identifying includes establishment of proof that the property was derived from, or used in,`
  line `the illicit traffic;`
  line
  line `(g) illegally acquired property", in relation to any person to whom this Chapter applies,`
  line means,--
  line
  line `(i) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Chapter, wholly or partly out of or by means of any income, earnings or assets derived or`
  line `obtained from or attributable to ^3[the contravention of any provisions ^4[`
  line `of this Act or the`
  line `equivalent value of such property; or]]`
  line
  line `(ii) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Chapter, for a consideration, or by any means wholly or partly traceable to any property referred`
  line `to in sub-clause (i) or the income or earning from ^5[such property or the equivalent value of such`
  line `property; or[`
  line
  line `^6[(iii) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of`
  line `the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances (Amendment) Act, 2014, wholly or partly out of`
  line `or by means of any income, earnings or assets the source of which cannot be proved, or the`
  line `equivalent value of such property,]`
  line
  line `and includes--`
  line
  line `(A) any property held by such person which would have been, in relation to any previous`
  line `holder thereof, illegally acquired property under this clause if such previous holder had not`
  line `ceased to hold it, unless such person or any other person who held the property at any time after`
  line `such previous holder or, where there are two or more such previous holders, the last of such`
  line `previous holders is or was a transferee in good faith for adequate consideration;`
  line
  line `(B) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Chapter, for a consideration, or by any means, wholly or partly traceable to any property falling`
  line `under item (A), or the income or earnings therefrom;`
  line
  line `^7[(h) "property" means any property or assets of every description, whether corporeal or`
  line `incorporeal, movable or immovable, tangible or intangible, wherever located and includes deeds and`
  line `instruments evidencing title to, or interest in, such property or assets;]`
  line
  line `(i) relative means`
  line
  line `(1) spouse of the person;`
  line
  line `(2) brother or sister of the person;`
  line
  line `(3) brother or sister of the spouse of the person;`
  line
  line `(4) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the person;`
  line
  line `(5) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the person;`
  line
  line `(6) spouse of a person referred to in sub-clause (2), sub-clause (3), sub-clause (4) or`
  line `sub-clause (5);`
  line
  line `(7) any lineal descendant of a person referred to in sub-clause (2) or sub-clause (3);`
  line
  line `(j) "tracing" means determining the nature, source, disposition, movement, title or ownership of`
  line property;
  line
  line `(k) "trust" includes any other legal obligation.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 227, for "for Forfeited Property constituted under" (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 32, for "illicit traffic" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s, 20, for "of this Act; or" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 20, for "such property", (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for clause (h) (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_c:
  sectionId (25188)
  sectionNo 68C
  orderNo 90
  title `Prohibition of holding illegally acquired property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25188&sectionno=68C&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[68C. Prohibition of holding illegally acquired property.-- (1) As from the commencement of this`
  line `Chapter, it shall not be lawful for any person to whom this Chapter applies to hold any illegally acquired`
  line `property either by himself or through any other person on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person holds any illegally acquired property in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), such property shall be liable to be forfeited to the Central Government in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that no property shall be forfeited under this Chapter if such property was acquired, by a`
  line `person to whom this Act applies, before a period of six years from the date he was arrested or against whom a warrant or authorisation of arrest has been issued for the commission of an offence punishable`
  line `under this Act or from the date the order or detention was issued, as the case may be.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 33, for "the proviso" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_d:
  sectionId (25189)
  sectionNo 68D
  orderNo 91
  title `Competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25189&sectionno=68D&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[68D. Competent authority.-- (1) The Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, authorise ^2[any Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Central Excise] or Commissioner`
  line `of Income-tax or any other officer of the Central Government of equivalent rank to perform the functions`
  line `of the competent authority under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authorities shall perform their functions in respect of such persons or classes of`
  line `persons as the Central Government may, by order, direct.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 21, for "any Collector of Customs or Collector of Central Excise" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_e:
  sectionId (25190)
  sectionNo 68E
  orderNo 92
  title `Identifying illegally acquired property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25190&sectionno=68E&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[68E. Identifying illegally acquired property.-- ^2(1) Every officer empowered under section 53 and`
  line `every officer-in-charge of a police station shall, or receipt of information is satisfied that any person to`
  line `whom this Chapter applies holds any illegally acquired property, he may, after recording reasons for`
  line `doing so, proceed to take all steps necessary for tracing and identifying such property.`
  line
  line `(2) The steps referred to in sub-section (1) may include any inquiry, investigation or survey in respect`
  line `of any person, place, property, assets, documents, books of account in any bank or public financial`
  line `institution or any other relevant matters.`
  line
  line `(3) Any inquiry, investigation or survey referred to in sub-section (2) shall be carried out by an officer`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1) in accordance with such directions or guidelines as the competent authority`
  line `may make or issue in this behalf.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 34, for sub- section (1) (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_f:
  sectionId (25191)
  sectionNo 68F
  orderNo 93
  title `Seizure or freezing of illegally acquired property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25191&sectionno=68F&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[68F. Seizure or freezing of illegally acquired property.-- (1) Where any officer conducting an`
  line `inquiry or investigation under section 68E has reason to believe that any property in relation to which`
  line `such inquiry or investigation is being conducted is an illegally acquired property and such property is`
  line `likely to be concealed, transferred or dealt with in any manner which will result in frustrating any`
  line `proceeding relating to forfeiture of such property under this Chapter, he may make an order for seizing`
  line `such property and where it is not practicable to seize such property, he may make an order that such`
  line `property shall not be transferred or otherwise dealt with, except with the prior permission of the officer`
  line `making such order, or of the competent authority and a copy of such order shall be served on the person`
  line `concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority shall be duly informed of any order made under this subsection`
  line `and a copy of such an order shall be sent to the competent authority within forty-eight hours of its`
  line `being made.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order made under sub-section (1) shall have no effect unless the said order is confirmed by an`
  line `order of the competent authority within a period of thirty days of its being made.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, "transfer of property" means any disposition,`
  line `conveyance, assignment, settlement, delivery, payment or other alienation of property and, without`
  line `limiting the generality of the foregoing, includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the creation of a trust in property;`
  line
  line `(b) the grant or creation of any lease, mortgage, charge, easement, licence, power, partnership or`
  line `interest in property;`
  line
  line `(c) the exercise of a power of appointment of property vested in any person, not the owner of the`
  line `property, to determine its disposition in favour of any person other than the donee of the power; and`
  line
  line `(d) any transaction entered into by any person with intent thereby to diminish directly or`
  line `indirectly the value of his own property and to increase the value of the property of any other person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_g:
  sectionId (25192)
  sectionNo 68G
  orderNo 94
  title `Management of properties seized or forfeited under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25192&sectionno=68G&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[68G. Management of properties seized or forfeited under this Chapter.-- (1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, appoint as many of its officers (not below the rank of a Joint secretary to the Government) as it thinks fit, to perform the functions of an`
  line Administrator.
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator appointed under sub-section (1) shall receive and manage the property in`
  line `relation to which an order has been made under sub-section (1) of section 68F or under section 68-I in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Administrator shall also take such measures, as the Central Government may direct, to`
  line `dispose of the property which is forfeited to the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_h:
  sectionId (25193)
  sectionNo 68H
  orderNo 95
  title `Notice of forfeiture of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25193&sectionno=68H&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[68H. Notice of forfeiture of property. -- (1) If, having regard to the value of the properties held by`
  line `any person to whom this Chapter applies, either by himself or through any other person on his behalf, his`
  line `known sources of income, earnings or assets, and any other information or material available to it as a`
  line `result of a report from any officer making an investigation under section 68E or otherwise, the competent`
  line `authority has reason to believe (the reasons for such belief to be recorded in writing) that all or any of`
  line `such properties are illegally acquired properties, it may serve a notice upon such person (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the person affected) calling upon him within a period of thirty days specified in the notice to`
  line `indicate the sources of his income, earnings or assets, out of which or by means of which he has acquired`
  line `such property, the evidence on which he relies and other relevant information and particulars, and to show`
  line `cause why all or any of such properties, as the case may be, should not be declared to be illegally acquired`
  line `properties and forfeited to the Central Government under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice under sub-section (1) to any person specifies any property as being held on behalf`
  line `of such person by any other person, a copy of the notice shall also be served upon such other person.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that no notice for forfeiture shall be served upon any person referred to in clause (cc) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 68A or relative of a person referred to in that clause or associate of a person`
  line `referred to in that clause or holder of any property which was at any time previously held by a person`
  line `referred to in that clause.]`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that in a case where the provisions of`
  line `section 68J are applicable, no notice under this section shall be invalid merely on the ground that it fails to`
  line `mention the evidence relied upon or it fails to establish a direct nexus between the property sought to be`
  line `forfeited and any activity in contravention of the provisions of this Act.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 35 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_i:
  sectionId (25417)
  sectionNo 68-I
  orderNo 96
  title `Forfeiture of property in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25417&sectionno=68-I&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[68-I. Forfeiture of property in certain cases. -- (1) The competent authority may, after considering`
  line `the explanation, if any, to the show cause notice issued under section 68H, and the materials available`
  line `before it and after giving to the person affected (and in a case where the person affected holds any`
  line `property specified in the notice through any other person, to such other person also) a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard, by order, record a finding whether all or any of the properties in question are`
  line `illegally acquired properties:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person affected (and in a case where the person affected holds any property`
  line `specified in the notice through any other person such other person also) does not appear before the`
  line `competent authority or represent his case before it within a period of thirty days specified in the show`
  line `cause notice, the competent authority may proceed to record a finding under this sub-section ex parte on`
  line `the basis of evidence available before it.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the competent authority is satisfied that some of the properties referred to in the show`
  line `cause notice are illegally acquired properties but is not able to identify specifically such properties, then,`
  line `it shall be lawful for the competent authority to specify the properties which, to the best of its judgment,`
  line `are illegally acquired properties and record a finding accordingly under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the competent authority records a finding under this section to the effect that any property`
  line `is illegally acquired property, it shall declare that such property shall, subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter, stand forfeited to the Central Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that no illegally acquired property of any person who is referred to in clause (cc) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 68A or relative of a person referred to in that clause or associate of a person`
  line `referred to in that clause or holder of any property which was at any time previously held by a person`
  line `referred to in that clause shall stand forefeited.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where any shares in a company stand forfeited to the Central Government under this Chapter,`
  line `then, the company shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or`
  line `the articles of association of the company, forthwith register the Central Government as the transferee of`
  line `such shares.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_i_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 36 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_j:
  sectionId (25418)
  sectionNo 68J
  orderNo 97
  title `Burden of proof`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25418&sectionno=68J&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[68J. Burden of proof.-- In any proceedings under this Chapter, the burden of proving that any`
  line `property specified in the notice served under section 68H is not illegally acquired property shall be on the`
  line `person affected.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_k:
  sectionId (25419)
  sectionNo 68K
  orderNo 98
  title `Fine in lieu of forfeiture`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_k_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25419&sectionno=68K&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[68K. Fine in lieu of forfeiture. -- (1) Where the competent authority makes a declaration that any`
  line `property stands forfeited to the Central Government under section 68-I and it is a case where the source of`
  line `only a part of the illegally acquired property has not been proved to the satisfaction of the competent`
  line `authority, it shall make an order giving an option to the person affected to pay, in lieu of forfeiture, a fine`
  line `equal to the market value of such part.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making an order imposing a fine under sub-section (1), the person affected shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the person affected pays the fine due under sub-section (1), within such time as may be`
  line `allowed in that behalf, the competent authority may, by order, revoke the declaration of forfeiture under`
  line `section 68-I and thereupon such property shall stand released.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_l:
  sectionId (25420)
  sectionNo 68L
  orderNo 99
  title `Procedure in relation to certain trust properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25420&sectionno=68L&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[68L. Procedure in relation to certain trust properties.-- In the case of any person referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (vi) of clause (b) of section 68B, if the competent authority, on the basis of the information and`
  line `materials available to it, has reason to believe (the reasons for such belief to be recorded in writing) that`
  line `any property held in trust is illegally acquired property, it may serve a notice upon the author of the trust`
  line `or, as the case may be, the contributor of the assets out of or by means of which such propery was`
  line `acquired by the trust and the trustees, calling upon them within a period of thirty days specified in the`
  line `notice, to explain the source of money or other assets out of or by means of which such property was`
  line `acquired or, as the case may be, the source of money or other assets which were contributed to the trust`
  line `for acquiring such property and thereupon such notice shall be deemed to be a notice served under section`
  line `68H and all the other provisions of this Chapter shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section "illegally acquired property", in relation to any`
  line `property held in trust, includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any property which if it had continued to be held by the author of the trust or the contributor of`
  line `such property to the trust would have been illegally acquired property in relation to such author or`
  line contributor;
  line
  line `(ii) any property acquired by the trust out of any contributions made by any person which would`
  line `have been illegally acquired property in relation to such person had such person acquired such`
  line `property out of such contributions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_m:
  sectionId (25421)
  sectionNo 68M
  orderNo 100
  title `Certain transfers to be null and void`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_m_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25421&sectionno=68M&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[68M. Certain transfers to be null and void.-- Where after the making of an order under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 68F or the issue of a notice under section 68H or under section 68L, any`
  line `property referred to in the said order or notice is transferred by any mode whatsoever such transfer shall,`
  line `for the purposes of the proceedings under this Chapter, be ignored and if such property is subsequently`
  line `forfeited to the Central Government under section 68-I, then, the transfer of such property shall be`
  line `deemed to be null and void.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_n:
  sectionId (25422)
  sectionNo 68N
  orderNo 101
  title `Constitution of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_n_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 227, for section 68N (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25422&sectionno=68N&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[68N. Constitution of Appellate Tribunal.-- The Appellate Tribunal constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 12 of the Smugglers and Foreign Exchange Manipulators (Forfeiture of Property) Act, 1976 (13 of 1976) shall be the Appellate Tribunal for hearing appeals against the orders`
  line `made under section 68F, section 68-I, sub-section (1) of section 68K or section 68L.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_o:
  sectionId (25423)
  sectionNo 68-O
  orderNo 102
  title Appeals
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_o_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_o_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25423&sectionno=68-O&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[68-O. Appeals.-- (1) ^2[Any officer referred to in sub-section (1) of section 68E or any person`
  line `aggrieved by an order of the competent authority] made under section 68F, section 68-I, sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 68K or section 68L, may, within forty-five days from the date on which the order is served on`
  line `him, prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the said period of forty-five days,`
  line `but not after sixty days, from the date aforesaid if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving an`
  line `opportunity to the appellant to be heard, if he so desires, and after making such further inquiry as it deems`
  line `fit, confirm, modify or set aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers and functions of the Appellate Tribunal may be exercised and discharged by Benches`
  line `consisting of three members and constituted by the Chairman of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), where the Chairman considers it necessary`
  line `so to do for the expeditious disposal of appeals under this section, he may constitute a Bench of two`
  line `members and a Bench so constituted may exercise and discharge the powers and functions of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the members of a Bench so constituted differ on any point or points, they shall state`
  line `the point or points on which they differ and refer the same to a third member (to be specified by the`
  line `Chairman) for hearing of such point or points and such point or points shall be decided according to the`
  line `opinion of that member.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that if the office of the Chairman is vacant by reason of his death, resignation or`
  line `otherwise, or if the Chairman is unable to discharge his duties owing to absence, illness or any other`
  line `cause, the Central Government may, by order, nominate any member to act as the Chairman until a new`
  line `Chairman is appointed and assumes charge or, as the case may be, resumes his duties.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal may regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(6) On application to the Appellate Tribunal and on payment of the prescribed fee, the Tribunal may`
  line `allow a party to any appeal or any person authorised in his behalf by such party to inspect at any time`
  line `during office hours, any relevant records and registers of the Tribunal and obtain a certified copy of any`
  line `part thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_o_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 37, for "any person aggrieved by an order of the competent authority" (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_p:
  sectionId (25424)
  sectionNo 68P
  orderNo 103
  title `Notice or order not to be invalid for error in description.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25424&sectionno=68P&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[68P. Notice or order not to be invalid for error in description.-- No notice issued or served, no`
  line `declaration made, and no order passed, under this Chapter shall be deemed to be invalid by reason of any`
  line `error in the description of the property or person mentioned therein if such property or person is`
  line `identifiable from the description so mentioned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_q:
  sectionId (25425)
  sectionNo 68Q
  orderNo 104
  title `Bar of jurisdiction`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_q_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25425&sectionno=68Q&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[68Q. Bar of jurisdiction.-- No order passed or declaration made under this Chapter shall be`
  line `appealable except as provided therein and no civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter`
  line `which the Appellate Tribunal or any competent authority is empowered by or under this Chapter to`
  line `determine, and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action`
  line `taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_r:
  sectionId (25426)
  sectionNo 68R
  orderNo 105
  title `Competent authority and Appellate Tribunal to have powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_r_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25426&sectionno=68R&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_r_content:
  string
  line `^1[68R. Competent authority and Appellate Tribunal to have powers of civil court.-- The`
  line `competent authority and the Appellate Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court while trying a`
  line `suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_s:
  sectionId (25427)
  sectionNo 68S
  orderNo 106
  title `Information to competent authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_s_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25427&sectionno=68S&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_s_content:
  string
  line `^1[68S. Information to competent authority.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `law, the competent authority shall have power to require any officer or authority of the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or a local authority to furnish information in relation to such persons,`
  line `points or matters as in the opinion of the competent authority will be useful for, or relevant to, the`
  line `purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer referred to in section 68T may furnish suo motu any information available with him`
  line `to the competent authority if in the opinion of the officer such information will be useful to the competent`
  line `authority for the purposes of this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_t:
  sectionId (25428)
  sectionNo 68T
  orderNo 107
  title `Certain officers to assist Administrator, competent authority and Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_t_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25428&sectionno=68T&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_t_content:
  string
  line `^1[68T. Certain officers to assist Administrator, competent authority and Appellate Tribunal -- For the purposes of any proceedings under this Chapter, the following officers are hereby empowered and`
  line `required to assist the Administrator appointed under section 68G, competent authority and the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) officers of the Narcotics Control Bureau;`
  line
  line `(b) officers of the Customs Department;`
  line
  line `(c) officers of the Central Excise Department;`
  line
  line `(d) officers of the Income-tax Department;`
  line
  line `(e) officers of enforcement appointed under the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973`
  line `(46 of 1973);`
  line
  line `(f) officers of police;`
  line
  line `(g) officers of the Narcotics Department;`
  line
  line `(h) officers of the Central Economic Intelligence Bureau;`
  line
  line `(i) officers of the Directorate of Revenue Intelligence;`
  line
  line `(j) such other officers of the Central or State Government as are specified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_u:
  sectionId (25429)
  sectionNo 68U
  orderNo 108
  title `Power to take possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_u_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25429&sectionno=68U&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_u_content:
  string
  line `^1[68U. Power to take possession.-- (1) Where any property has been declared to be forfeited to the`
  line `Central Government under this Chapter, or where the person affected has failed to pay the fine due under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 68K within the time allowed therefor under sub-section (3) of that section, the`
  line `competent authority may order the person affected as well as any other person who may be in possession`
  line `of the property to surrender or deliver possession thereof to the Administrator appointed under section`
  line `68G or to any person duly authorised by him in this behalf within thirty days of the service of the order.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person refuses or fails to comply with an order made under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Administrator may take possession of the property and may for that purpose use such force as may be`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Administrator may, for the purpose of`
  line `taking possession of any property referred to in sub-section (1), requisition the service of any police`
  line `officer to assist him and it shall be the duty of such officer to comply with such requisition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_v:
  sectionId (25430)
  sectionNo 68V
  orderNo 109
  title `Rectification of mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_v_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25430&sectionno=68V&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_v_content:
  string
  line `^1[68V. Rectification of mistakes.-- With a view to rectifying any mistakes apparent from record, the`
  line `competent authority or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, may amend any order made by it`
  line `within a period of one year from the date of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such amendment is likely to affect any person prejudicially, it shall not be made`
  line `without giving to such person a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_w:
  sectionId (25431)
  sectionNo 68W
  orderNo 110
  title `Findings under other laws not conclusive for proceedings under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_w_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25431&sectionno=68W&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_w_content:
  string
  line `^1[68W. Findings under other laws not conclusive for proceedings under this Chapter. -- No finding`
  line `of any officer or authority under any other law shall be conclusive for the purposes of any proceedings`
  line `under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_x:
  sectionId (25432)
  sectionNo 68X
  orderNo 111
  title `Service of notices and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_x_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25432&sectionno=68X&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_x_content:
  string
  line `^1[68X. Service of notices and orders.-- Any notice or order issued or made under this Chapter shall`
  line `be served--`
  line
  line `(a) by tendering the notice or order or sending it by registered post to the person for whom it is`
  line `intended or to his agent;`
  line
  line `(b) if the notice or order cannot be served in the manner provided in clause (a), by affixing it on a`
  line `conspicuous place in the property in relation to which the notice or order is issued or made or on`
  line `some conspicuous part of the premises in which the person for whom it is intended is known to have`
  line `last resided or carried on business or personally worked for gain.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_y:
  sectionId (25433)
  sectionNo 68Y
  orderNo 112
  title `Punishment for acquiring property in relation to which proceedings have been taken, under this Chapter`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_y_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25433&sectionno=68Y&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_y_content:
  string
  line `^1[68Y. Punishment for acquiring property in relation to which proceedings have been taken,`
  line `under this Chapter.-- Any person who knowingly acquired, by any mode whatsoever, any property in`
  line `relation to which proceedings are pending under this Chapter shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years and with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_z:
  sectionId (25434)
  sectionNo 68Z
  orderNo 113
  title `Release of property in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_z_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 38 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25434&sectionno=68Z&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_68_z_content:
  string
  line `^1[68Z. Release of property in certain cases. -- (1) Where the detention order of a detenu is set aside`
  line `or withdrawn, properties seized or frozen under this Chapter shall stand released.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (cc) of sub-section (2) of section`
  line `68A has been acquitted or discharged from the charges under this Act or any other corresponding law of`
  line `any other country and the acquittal was not appealed against or when appealed against, the appeal was`
  line `disposed of as a consequence of which such property could not be forfeited or warrant of arrest or`
  line `authorisation of arrest issued against such person has been withdrawn, then, property seized or frozen`
  line `under this Chapter shall stand released.]`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (25435)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 114
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25435&sectionno=69&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or a State Government or any officer of the Central Government or of`
  line `the State Government or any other person exercising any powers or discharging any functions or`
  line `performing any duties under this Act, for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this`
  line `Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (25436)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 115
  title `Central Government and State Government to have regard to international conventions while making rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25436&sectionno=70&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Wherever under this Act the Central Government or the State Government has`
  line `been empowered to make rules, the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `subject to other provisions of this Act, may while making the rules have regard to the provisions of the`
  line `Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs, 1961, the Protocol of 1972 amending the said Convention and of`
  line `the Convention on Psychotropic Substances, 1971 to which India is a party and to the provisions of any`
  line `other international convention relating to narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances to which India may`
  line `become a party.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (25437)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 116
  title `Power of Government to establish centres for identification, treatment, etc., of addicts and for supply of narcotic drug and psychotropic substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25437&sectionno=71&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[The Government may establish,`
  line `recognise or approve as many centres as it thinks fit for identification, treatment, managemen], education,`
  line `after-care, rehabilitation, social re-integration of addicts and for supply, subject to such conditions and in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed, by the concerned Government of any narcotic drugs and psychotropic`
  line `substances to the addicts registered with the Government and to others where such supply is a medical`
  line necessity.
  line
  line `(2) The Government may make rules consistent with this Act providing for the establishment,`
  line `appointment, maintenance, management and superintendence of, and for supply of narcotic drugs and`
  line `psychotropic substances from, the centres referred to in sub-section (1) and for the appointment, training,`
  line `powers, duties and persons employed in such centres.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2014, s. 24, for "The Government may, in its discretion, establish as many centres as it thinks fit for`
  line `identification, treatment" (w.e.f. 1-5-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (25438)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 117
  title `Recovery of sums due to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25438&sectionno=72&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) In respect of any licence fee or other sum of any`
  line `kind payable to the Central Government or to the State Government under any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act or of any rule or order made thereunder, the officer of the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, who is empowered to require the payment of such sum, may deduct the`
  line `amount of such sum from any money owing to the person from whom such sum may be recoverable or`
  line `due or may recover such amount or sum by attachment and sale of the goods belonging to such persons`
  line `and if the amount of the same is not so recovered, the same may be recovered from the person or from his`
  line `surety (if any) as if it were an arrears of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) When any person, in compliance with any rule made under this Act, gives a bond (other than a`
  line `bond under section 34 and section 39) for the performance of any act, or for his abstention from any act,`
  line `such performance or abstention shall be deemed to be a public duty within the meaning of section 74 of`
  line `the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872); and upon breach of the conditions of such bond by him, the`
  line `whole sum named therein as the amount to be paid in case of such breach may be recovered from him or`
  line `from his surety (if any) as if it were an arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (25439)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 118
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25439&sectionno=73&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall entertain any suit or proceeding against any decision`
  line `made or order passed by any officer or authority under this Act or under any rule made thereunder on any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) withholding, refusal or cancellation of any licence for the cultivation of the opium poppy;`
  line
  line `(b) weighment, examination and classification according to the quality and consistence of opium`
  line `and any deductions from, or addition to, the standard price made in accordance with such`
  line examination;
  line
  line `(c) confiscation of opium found to be adulterated with any foreign substance.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (25440)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 119
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25440&sectionno=74&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Every officer or other employee of the Government exercising or`
  line `performing, immediately before the commencement of this Act, any powers or duties with respect to any`
  line `matters provided for in this Act, shall on such commencement, be deemed to have been appointed under`
  line `the relevant provisions of this Act to the same post and with the same designation as he was holding`
  line `immediately before such commencement`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74_a:
  sectionId (25441)
  sectionNo 74A
  orderNo 120
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 20 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25441&sectionno=74A&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_74_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[74A. Power of Central Government to give directions. -- The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions as it may deem necessary to a State Government regarding the carrying into execution of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, and the State Government shall comply with such directions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (25442)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 121
  title `Power to delegate`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25442&sectionno=75&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `delegate, subject to such conditions and limitations as may be specified in the notification, such of its`
  line `powers and functions under this Act (except the power to make rules) as it may deem necessary or`
  line `expedient, to the Board or any other authority or the Narcotics Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, delegate, subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations as may be specified in the notification, such of its powers and functions under`
  line `this Act (except the power to make rules) as it may deem necessary or expedient, to any authority or`
  line `officer of that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (25443)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 122
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25443&sectionno=76&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the method by which percentages in the case of liquid preparations shall be calculated for the`
  line `purposes of clauses (v), (vi) (xiv) and (xv) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the form of bond to keep the peace to be executed under section 34;`
  line
  line `(c) the form of bond to be executed for release of an addict convict for medical treatment under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 39 and the bond to be executed by such convict before his release after due`
  line `admonition under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) the manner in which controlled delivery under section 50A is to be undertaken;]`
  line
  line `(d) the authority or the person by whom and the manner in which a document received from any`
  line `place outside India shall be authenticated under clause (ii) of section 66;`
  line
  line `^2[(da) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which properties shall be managed by`
  line `the Administrator under sub-section (2) of section 68G;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(dc) the fees which shall be paid for the inspection of the records and registers of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal or for obtaining the certified copy of any part thereof under sub-section (6) of section 68-O;`
  line
  line `(dd) the powers of a civil court that may be exercised by the competent authority and the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal under clause (f) of section 68R;`
  line
  line `(de) the disposal of all articles or things confiscated under this Act;`
  line
  line `(df) the drawing of samples and testing and analysis of such samples;`
  line
  line `(dg) the rewards to be paid to the officers, informers and other persons;]`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions and the manner in which narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances may be`
  line `supplied for medical necessity to the addicts registered with the Central Government and to others`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 71;`
  line
  line `(f) the establishment, appointment, maintenance, management and superintendence of centres`
  line `established by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 71 and appointment, training,`
  line `powers and duties of persons employed in such centres;`
  line
  line `(g) the term of office of, the manner of filling casual vacancies of, and the allowances payable to,`
  line `the Chairman and members of the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Consultative`
  line `Committee and the conditions and restrictions subject to which a non-member may be appointed to a`
  line `sub-committee under sub-section (5) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 39 (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 21 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (db) omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 227 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016)`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (25444)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 123
  title `Rules and notifications to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2001, s. 40, for certain words, brackets, figures and letter (w.e.f. 2-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25444&sectionno=77&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `^1[Every rule made under this Act by the`
  line `Central Government and every notification or order issued under clause (viia), clause (xi), clause (xxiiia)`
  line `of section 2, section 3, section 7A, section 9A and clause (a) of section 27 shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be, after it is made or issued], before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or both Houses agree that the rule or`
  line `notification should not be made or issued, the rule or the notification shall thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (25445)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 124
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25445&sectionno=78&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the`
  line `State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions and the manner in which narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances shall be`
  line `supplied for medical necessity to the addicts registered with the State Government and others under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 71;`
  line
  line `(b) the establishment, appointment, maintenance, management, superintendence of centres`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 71 and appointment, training, powers and duties of`
  line `persons employed in such centres;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by a State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the Legislature of that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (25446)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 125
  title `Application of the Customs Act, 1962.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25446&sectionno=79&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `All prohibitions and restrictions imposed by or under`
  line `this Act on the import into India, the export from India and transhipment of narcotic drugs and`
  line `psychotropic substances shall be deemed to be prohibitions and restrictions imposed by or under the`
  line `Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) and the provisions of that Act shall apply accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the doing of anything is an offence punishable under that Act and under this Act,`
  line `nothing in that Act or in this section shall prevent the offender from being punished under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (25447)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 126
  title `Application of the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940 not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25447&sectionno=80&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, the Drugs and Cosmetics Act,`
  line `1940 (23 of 1940) or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (25448)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 127
  title `Saving of State and special laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25448&sectionno=81&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act or in the rules made thereunder shall`
  line `affect the validity of any Provincial Act or an Act of any State Legislature for the time being in force, or`
  line `of any rule made thereunder which imposes any restriction or provides for a punishment not imposed by`
  line `or provided for under this Act or imposes a restriction or provides for a punishment greater in degree than`
  line `a corresponding restriction imposed by or a corresponding punishment provided for by or under this Act`
  line `for the cultivation of cannabis plant or consumption of, or traffic in, any narcotic drug or psychotropic`
  line `substance within India.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (25449)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 128
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25449&sectionno=82&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Opium Act, 1857 (13 of 1857), the Opium Act, 1878 (1 of 1878)`
  line `and the Dangerous Drugs Act, 1930 (2 of 1930) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or`
  line `taken under any of the enactments repealed by sub-section (1) shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with`
  line `the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (25450)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 129
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222&sectionId=25450&sectionno=83&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00029_198561_1517807326222
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the date on`
  line `which this Act receives the assent of the President.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before the`
  line `Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
